WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.409 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.409 --> 00:00:10.230 align:middle line:90%


00:00:10.230 --> 00:00:13.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:13.180 --> 00:00:17.420 align:middle line:84%
And we are so lucky
to be alive right now.

00:00:17.420 --> 00:00:21.490 align:middle line:84%
Think of all the access that
we have to spiritual teachings

00:00:21.490 --> 00:00:23.310 align:middle line:90%
and experiences.

00:00:23.310 --> 00:00:25.520 align:middle line:84%
And this is just causing
more and more people

00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:30.040 align:middle line:84%
to become more aware,
more awake, more conscious

00:00:30.040 --> 00:00:32.200 align:middle line:90%
every single day.

00:00:32.200 --> 00:00:33.980 align:middle line:84%
So maybe you're in
the place in your life

00:00:33.980 --> 00:00:35.740 align:middle line:90%
when you are done searching.

00:00:35.740 --> 00:00:39.330 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you're done looking for
that thing outside yourself

00:00:39.330 --> 00:00:40.890 align:middle line:84%
to fulfill you,
and you're really

00:00:40.890 --> 00:00:45.490 align:middle line:84%
ready to be truly free
and truly of contribution

00:00:45.490 --> 00:00:48.310 align:middle line:84%
because you found
what you're looking

00:00:48.310 --> 00:00:51.017 align:middle line:90%
for is right inside of you.

00:00:51.017 --> 00:00:52.600 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're
talking about today.

00:00:52.600 --> 00:00:54.430 align:middle line:90%
It's called awakening.

00:00:54.430 --> 00:00:56.490 align:middle line:90%
And Arjuna Ardagh is here.

00:00:56.490 --> 00:00:58.540 align:middle line:90%
He is an awakening coach.

00:00:58.540 --> 00:01:00.670 align:middle line:90%
He's the author of eight books.

00:01:00.670 --> 00:01:03.080 align:middle line:90%
His latest is "Better Than Sex."

00:01:03.080 --> 00:01:05.730 align:middle line:84%
And he also trains
people to become

00:01:05.730 --> 00:01:07.870 align:middle line:90%
facilitators of awakening.

00:01:07.870 --> 00:01:08.910 align:middle line:90%
I'm so glad you're here.

00:01:08.910 --> 00:01:10.210 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for being here today.

00:01:10.210 --> 00:01:12.710 align:middle line:84%
>>ARJUNA ARDAGH: It's a great
pleasure to be with you again.

00:01:12.710 --> 00:01:15.043 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So can we start a
little bit about your journey?

00:01:15.043 --> 00:01:17.410 align:middle line:84%
About your journey
into awakening.

00:01:17.410 --> 00:01:19.060 align:middle line:90%
Where were you before that?

00:01:19.060 --> 00:01:20.110 align:middle line:90%
Were you searching?

00:01:20.110 --> 00:01:21.480 align:middle line:90%
Were you found?

00:01:21.480 --> 00:01:22.345 align:middle line:90%
Where were you?

00:01:22.345 --> 00:01:22.970 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:01:22.970 --> 00:01:29.450 align:middle line:84%
Well, Lisa, I think just
like for anybody in this way,

00:01:29.450 --> 00:01:31.800 align:middle line:90%
it starts with suffering.

00:01:31.800 --> 00:01:33.739 align:middle line:90%
That's the initial motivation.

00:01:33.739 --> 00:01:35.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's the human journey.

00:01:35.030 --> 00:01:36.030 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Right.

00:01:36.030 --> 00:01:39.770 align:middle line:84%
So I was born in
London in the 1950s.

00:01:39.770 --> 00:01:41.530 align:middle line:84%
I would say into a
family where there

00:01:41.530 --> 00:01:44.000 align:middle line:84%
was an above average
level of suffering.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:44.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, OK.

00:01:44.900 --> 00:01:46.900 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: I had kind of
super enhanced suffering

00:01:46.900 --> 00:01:48.130 align:middle line:90%
in my family.

00:01:48.130 --> 00:01:48.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:01:48.630 --> 00:01:50.950 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: So there was
a lot of mental illness

00:01:50.950 --> 00:01:53.140 align:middle line:84%
and suicide and
depression in my family.

00:01:53.140 --> 00:01:59.842 align:middle line:84%
So when you're a little kid, you
don't really know about that.

00:01:59.842 --> 00:02:01.300 align:middle line:84%
Your family is your
family and then

00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:03.850 align:middle line:84%
the outside world is
beyond your family.

00:02:03.850 --> 00:02:05.700 align:middle line:84%
But when you get
to be a teenager,

00:02:05.700 --> 00:02:07.705 align:middle line:90%
you start to individuate.

00:02:07.705 --> 00:02:09.830 align:middle line:84%
And then you can look at
your family in a fresh way

00:02:09.830 --> 00:02:12.780 align:middle line:84%
and actually you're able to
evaluate the deck of cards

00:02:12.780 --> 00:02:14.760 align:middle line:90%
that you've been dealt.

00:02:14.760 --> 00:02:17.560 align:middle line:84%
So it was actually
at that time, when

00:02:17.560 --> 00:02:22.620 align:middle line:84%
I got to be 14, for the
first time I realized, wow,

00:02:22.620 --> 00:02:25.160 align:middle line:90%
this is not a pretty picture.

00:02:25.160 --> 00:02:28.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: This is not normal.

00:02:28.090 --> 00:02:32.370 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: I realized if I
just go along the same route

00:02:32.370 --> 00:02:36.550 align:middle line:84%
that my fam-- that
is genetic to me,

00:02:36.550 --> 00:02:39.780 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to either commit
suicide or go crazy.

00:02:39.780 --> 00:02:40.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:02:40.870 --> 00:02:41.790 align:middle line:90%
Stakes were high.

00:02:41.790 --> 00:02:43.100 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: The stakes were high.

00:02:43.100 --> 00:02:46.230 align:middle line:90%
So this was 1971 when I was 14.

00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:49.832 align:middle line:84%
So I was-- I started
to look around.

00:02:49.832 --> 00:02:50.540 align:middle line:90%
What's available?

00:02:50.540 --> 00:02:53.480 align:middle line:84%
What can you do
to heal your mind?

00:02:53.480 --> 00:02:55.530 align:middle line:84%
So the obvious thing
was psychotherapy and

00:02:55.530 --> 00:03:01.180 align:middle line:84%
psychoanalysis which both my
parents had friends in that.

00:03:01.180 --> 00:03:04.880 align:middle line:84%
But as soon as I met
a few psychoanalysts

00:03:04.880 --> 00:03:07.330 align:middle line:84%
and psychotherapists,
even at that young age,

00:03:07.330 --> 00:03:10.750 align:middle line:84%
I realized they were in worse
trouble than their patients.

00:03:10.750 --> 00:03:13.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's
interesting as a teenager.

00:03:13.030 --> 00:03:15.430 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: So I looked
around what else was there.

00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:17.160 align:middle line:84%
There was the Hare
Krishnas, right,

00:03:17.160 --> 00:03:19.089 align:middle line:84%
going down Oxford
Street in 1971.

00:03:19.089 --> 00:03:19.630 align:middle line:90%
Hare Krishna.

00:03:19.630 --> 00:03:20.650 align:middle line:90%
Hare Krishna.

00:03:20.650 --> 00:03:22.626 align:middle line:90%
With their little thing.

00:03:22.626 --> 00:03:24.000 align:middle line:84%
And so I thought,
well, they were

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:26.210 align:middle line:84%
talking about
enlightenment and Krishna

00:03:26.210 --> 00:03:27.950 align:middle line:84%
and I thought,
great, that sounds

00:03:27.950 --> 00:03:30.120 align:middle line:84%
like the mega dose
I'm looking for.

00:03:30.120 --> 00:03:31.660 align:middle line:84%
So I went to my
mother and I said,

00:03:31.660 --> 00:03:33.910 align:middle line:84%
I've decided I'm going to
become a Hare Krishna, which

00:03:33.910 --> 00:03:35.740 align:middle line:90%
I thought was really good news.

00:03:35.740 --> 00:03:37.890 align:middle line:84%
She threatened an
immediate overdose

00:03:37.890 --> 00:03:40.510 align:middle line:90%
if I did anything like it.

00:03:40.510 --> 00:03:44.370 align:middle line:84%
So we did a compromise
and I learned

00:03:44.370 --> 00:03:46.040 align:middle line:84%
transcendental
meditation, and that's

00:03:46.040 --> 00:03:47.110 align:middle line:90%
what really got me going.

00:03:47.110 --> 00:03:49.330 align:middle line:90%
I did that for many, many years.

00:03:49.330 --> 00:03:51.640 align:middle line:84%
And that was really
what started it

00:03:51.640 --> 00:03:56.630 align:middle line:84%
for me was I realized my psyche
was in such enormous disrepair

00:03:56.630 --> 00:04:00.330 align:middle line:84%
that there was no way to fix
it through traditional methods.

00:04:00.330 --> 00:04:03.150 align:middle line:84%
I was going to need to actually
transcend it completely.

00:04:03.150 --> 00:04:05.370 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I was--
really got interested

00:04:05.370 --> 00:04:06.460 align:middle line:90%
when I was a teenager.

00:04:06.460 --> 00:04:08.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, that
explains a lot.

00:04:08.510 --> 00:04:11.430 align:middle line:84%
That right there, to
transcend the normal,

00:04:11.430 --> 00:04:15.700 align:middle line:84%
even-- especially to
transcend the broken.

00:04:15.700 --> 00:04:19.040 align:middle line:84%
That is a great
definition of awakening.

00:04:19.040 --> 00:04:20.620 align:middle line:90%
Transcendence.

00:04:20.620 --> 00:04:24.584 align:middle line:84%
And did you follow different
teachers at the time?

00:04:24.584 --> 00:04:25.250 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: I did.

00:04:25.250 --> 00:04:26.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How long were
you in that process for?

00:04:26.980 --> 00:04:28.313 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Well, it was 20 years.

00:04:28.313 --> 00:04:29.040 align:middle line:90%
20 years.

00:04:29.040 --> 00:04:31.580 align:middle line:90%
From 14 to 34.

00:04:31.580 --> 00:04:34.920 align:middle line:84%
I was really like
a full time seeker.

00:04:34.920 --> 00:04:37.470 align:middle line:84%
And there's a certain lifestyle
that goes along with that.

00:04:37.470 --> 00:04:38.730 align:middle line:90%
There's a way you meet people.

00:04:38.730 --> 00:04:40.271 align:middle line:84%
You don't say, how
you doing anymore.

00:04:40.271 --> 00:04:41.860 align:middle line:90%
You say "namaste."

00:04:41.860 --> 00:04:45.410 align:middle line:84%
And you eat certain food
and you've got a yoga mat.

00:04:45.410 --> 00:04:47.230 align:middle line:84%
There's a whole
kind of thing goes

00:04:47.230 --> 00:04:52.930 align:middle line:84%
with being a-- rather like
being a football enthusiast.

00:04:52.930 --> 00:04:54.841 align:middle line:84%
There's a certain
lifestyle goes with it.

00:04:54.841 --> 00:04:55.590 align:middle line:90%
Or being a surfer.

00:04:55.590 --> 00:04:58.980 align:middle line:84%
So being a spiritual seeker
there's a lifestyle involved.

00:04:58.980 --> 00:05:00.820 align:middle line:90%
So I did that very thoroughly.

00:05:00.820 --> 00:05:02.290 align:middle line:90%
I lived in India.

00:05:02.290 --> 00:05:04.350 align:middle line:90%
Whatever you could do, I did it.

00:05:04.350 --> 00:05:07.760 align:middle line:84%
And so wind the clock
forward to when I was 34.

00:05:07.760 --> 00:05:09.740 align:middle line:90%
This is 1991.

00:05:09.740 --> 00:05:12.940 align:middle line:84%
And I realized, you know, this
was like a hamster in a wheel.

00:05:12.940 --> 00:05:17.200 align:middle line:84%
That this seeking for a
state of enlightenment, which

00:05:17.200 --> 00:05:19.870 align:middle line:84%
is a concept that everybody
was holding in their mind,

00:05:19.870 --> 00:05:22.820 align:middle line:84%
that we've got to
enlightened, you know.

00:05:22.820 --> 00:05:24.670 align:middle line:84%
This hamster wheel,
it was actually

00:05:24.670 --> 00:05:26.450 align:middle line:90%
not really going anywhere.

00:05:26.450 --> 00:05:30.360 align:middle line:84%
It was just continuous movement
of working on yourself.

00:05:30.360 --> 00:05:34.550 align:middle line:84%
And that was when I met
an old man in India,

00:05:34.550 --> 00:05:40.690 align:middle line:84%
in Uttar Pradesh, who was not
really part of that whole game.

00:05:40.690 --> 00:05:42.670 align:middle line:90%
He was very rough.

00:05:42.670 --> 00:05:44.085 align:middle line:90%
He was a retired army officer.

00:05:44.085 --> 00:05:46.720 align:middle line:90%
His name is H.W.L. Poonja.

00:05:46.720 --> 00:05:51.230 align:middle line:84%
He was a retired army officer
who was really quite impatient

00:05:51.230 --> 00:05:53.980 align:middle line:84%
and didn't give any
teachings at all.

00:05:53.980 --> 00:05:56.800 align:middle line:84%
The first day I met him,
there was about eight people

00:05:56.800 --> 00:05:59.620 align:middle line:84%
in his living room
sitting on the floor.

00:05:59.620 --> 00:06:01.560 align:middle line:90%
And he was staring into space.

00:06:01.560 --> 00:06:04.780 align:middle line:84%
He was looking very kind
of bored and annoyed

00:06:04.780 --> 00:06:06.190 align:middle line:90%
by the whole thing.

00:06:06.190 --> 00:06:08.280 align:middle line:84%
And so finally I
got to speak to him

00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:09.810 align:middle line:90%
and he said, what do you want?

00:06:09.810 --> 00:06:11.670 align:middle line:90%
What do you want?

00:06:11.670 --> 00:06:13.240 align:middle line:84%
And I was a bit on
the spot because I

00:06:13.240 --> 00:06:14.740 align:middle line:84%
thought it was
obvious what I wanted

00:06:14.740 --> 00:06:16.980 align:middle line:84%
as part of this whole
spiritual seeking thing.

00:06:16.980 --> 00:06:18.110 align:middle line:90%
He said, what do you want?

00:06:18.110 --> 00:06:21.470 align:middle line:84%
So I said, well,
I said to him, I

00:06:21.470 --> 00:06:26.440 align:middle line:84%
feel like I've been seeking
as long as I can remember.

00:06:26.440 --> 00:06:29.302 align:middle line:84%
I said, what is in
the way of finding?

00:06:29.302 --> 00:06:33.320 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at me like it
was the most utterly stupid

00:06:33.320 --> 00:06:35.320 align:middle line:84%
question anybody had ever
asked him in his life.

00:06:35.320 --> 00:06:39.570 align:middle line:84%
He looked at me like, he said,
what's in the way of finding?

00:06:39.570 --> 00:06:42.080 align:middle line:90%
Seeking, of course.

00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:46.160 align:middle line:84%
And we can sit here in
2014 and laugh about that,

00:06:46.160 --> 00:06:50.840 align:middle line:84%
but I tell you, at that time it
completely put me into a spin

00:06:50.840 --> 00:06:54.450 align:middle line:84%
because I didn't know
anything else by that point.

00:06:54.450 --> 00:06:56.080 align:middle line:84%
My entire life
was about seeking.

00:06:56.080 --> 00:06:58.205 align:middle line:84%
And he was telling me that
seeking was the problem.

00:06:58.205 --> 00:07:01.740 align:middle line:90%


00:07:01.740 --> 00:07:05.080 align:middle line:84%
So I had one more conversation
with him that morning.

00:07:05.080 --> 00:07:07.240 align:middle line:84%
And, again, he looked
at me and he just

00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:10.020 align:middle line:84%
looked to me very intensely
and said, what do you want?

00:07:10.020 --> 00:07:12.460 align:middle line:84%
So I gave him the answer we'd
all been trained to give.

00:07:12.460 --> 00:07:13.740 align:middle line:84%
It was what we had been
conditioned to believe.

00:07:13.740 --> 00:07:14.980 align:middle line:90%
I want to be enlightened.

00:07:14.980 --> 00:07:15.990 align:middle line:90%
I want to be free.

00:07:15.990 --> 00:07:17.531 align:middle line:84%
No, I said, I want
to be enlightened.

00:07:17.531 --> 00:07:18.509 align:middle line:90%
He said, what's that?

00:07:18.509 --> 00:07:20.300 align:middle line:84%
Which I thought was an
interesting question

00:07:20.300 --> 00:07:20.924 align:middle line:90%
from a teacher.

00:07:20.924 --> 00:07:22.610 align:middle line:90%
What's that?

00:07:22.610 --> 00:07:25.460 align:middle line:90%
I said, well, I want to be free.

00:07:25.460 --> 00:07:26.730 align:middle line:90%
He said, OK.

00:07:26.730 --> 00:07:28.580 align:middle line:90%
He said, OK.

00:07:28.580 --> 00:07:34.380 align:middle line:84%
You show me the one who is
bound, and I will make it free.

00:07:34.380 --> 00:07:35.630 align:middle line:90%
I thought that's a great deal.

00:07:35.630 --> 00:07:39.260 align:middle line:84%
I've just got to show him my
ego and he'll set it free.

00:07:39.260 --> 00:07:40.380 align:middle line:90%
Fantastic.

00:07:40.380 --> 00:07:42.600 align:middle line:84%
So I thought this was deal
of the century, you know.

00:07:42.600 --> 00:07:46.030 align:middle line:84%
So I went back to my hotel
room to try and find the ego,

00:07:46.030 --> 00:07:46.880 align:middle line:90%
you see?

00:07:46.880 --> 00:07:48.005 align:middle line:90%
And this took about a week.

00:07:48.005 --> 00:07:51.180 align:middle line:90%


00:07:51.180 --> 00:07:55.350 align:middle line:84%
But the more I was looking
for this bound entity,

00:07:55.350 --> 00:07:57.352 align:middle line:84%
all I could find was
thoughts, was just

00:07:57.352 --> 00:07:58.810 align:middle line:84%
thoughts and thoughts
and thoughts.

00:07:58.810 --> 00:08:01.430 align:middle line:84%
And after a while,
the thoughts stopped

00:08:01.430 --> 00:08:04.100 align:middle line:90%
actually making any coherence.

00:08:04.100 --> 00:08:06.010 align:middle line:90%
They were just random thoughts.

00:08:06.010 --> 00:08:08.700 align:middle line:84%
Apple pie, a movie
I saw, Mary Poppins.

00:08:08.700 --> 00:08:10.872 align:middle line:90%
Just all this stuff going on.

00:08:10.872 --> 00:08:13.330 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you were looking
for the physical manifestation

00:08:13.330 --> 00:08:13.860 align:middle line:90%
of the ego?

00:08:13.860 --> 00:08:14.970 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: I don't know
what I was looking for.

00:08:14.970 --> 00:08:17.178 align:middle line:84%
What I realized was I had
no idea what's going on at,

00:08:17.178 --> 00:08:18.270 align:middle line:90%
you see.

00:08:18.270 --> 00:08:20.770 align:middle line:90%
I was lost.

00:08:20.770 --> 00:08:24.055 align:middle line:84%
But he had told me I had to
find this thing that was bound

00:08:24.055 --> 00:08:25.690 align:middle line:90%
and he would make it free.

00:08:25.690 --> 00:08:29.890 align:middle line:84%
So after six days-- today
it takes like 30 seconds,

00:08:29.890 --> 00:08:35.330 align:middle line:84%
but I was a difficult case--
so after six days, I woke up.

00:08:35.330 --> 00:08:38.764 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't really sleeping, but
I kind of woke up from resting,

00:08:38.764 --> 00:08:41.510 align:middle line:84%
you know, a little bit
refreshed after the night.

00:08:41.510 --> 00:08:42.010 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:08:42.010 --> 00:08:43.340 align:middle line:84%
There's something
I've got to do.

00:08:43.340 --> 00:08:44.631 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you've got to find the ego.

00:08:44.631 --> 00:08:46.470 align:middle line:90%
Got to find the ego.

00:08:46.470 --> 00:08:48.510 align:middle line:84%
So it was as though
a hand went back

00:08:48.510 --> 00:08:53.250 align:middle line:84%
into whatever was there
to find this thing,

00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:58.010 align:middle line:84%
and the hand just went on and
on and on and on and on forever.

00:08:58.010 --> 00:08:59.420 align:middle line:90%
And there was just space.

00:08:59.420 --> 00:09:02.960 align:middle line:90%
Just empty space.

00:09:02.960 --> 00:09:06.280 align:middle line:84%
And then in that moment
there was a recognition--

00:09:06.280 --> 00:09:07.710 align:middle line:90%
it's always been like that.

00:09:07.710 --> 00:09:09.810 align:middle line:90%
Everything else was made up.

00:09:09.810 --> 00:09:12.960 align:middle line:84%
There was never a thing called
an ego, it was just a concept

00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:13.561 align:middle line:90%
created by--

00:09:13.561 --> 00:09:14.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A concept.

00:09:14.310 --> 00:09:16.320 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: --Freud's
translator, actually,

00:09:16.320 --> 00:09:18.620 align:middle line:90%
that got into the popular lingo.

00:09:18.620 --> 00:09:20.620 align:middle line:84%
That there's never
been this thing.

00:09:20.620 --> 00:09:22.257 align:middle line:90%
There's always been this space.

00:09:22.257 --> 00:09:23.715 align:middle line:84%
And it was a very
clear recognition

00:09:23.715 --> 00:09:25.270 align:middle line:84%
that the whole
thing was made up.

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:27.480 align:middle line:84%
The whole seeking,
of being bound,

00:09:27.480 --> 00:09:28.820 align:middle line:90%
the whole thing was made up.

00:09:28.820 --> 00:09:31.470 align:middle line:84%
It was a story that
we get trapped in.

00:09:31.470 --> 00:09:34.810 align:middle line:84%
And when you actually wake up
from believing in that story,

00:09:34.810 --> 00:09:37.940 align:middle line:84%
there is just space,
which is free,

00:09:37.940 --> 00:09:40.290 align:middle line:84%
which is full of love,
which is full of creativity.

00:09:40.290 --> 00:09:43.920 align:middle line:84%
And I tell you, I sat on
the bed and involuntarily

00:09:43.920 --> 00:09:49.120 align:middle line:84%
my body just laughed for
like 25 minutes straight.

00:09:49.120 --> 00:09:50.190 align:middle line:90%
It was like a joke.

00:09:50.190 --> 00:09:51.680 align:middle line:90%
Getting a joke.

00:09:51.680 --> 00:09:53.722 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: A joke and the
joke was on you literally.

00:09:53.722 --> 00:09:55.429 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: The joke is
on all of us, yeah.

00:09:55.429 --> 00:09:57.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What did you mean
by Freud's translator?

00:09:57.830 --> 00:10:00.440 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Well, Freud,
of course, spoke German.

00:10:00.440 --> 00:10:03.160 align:middle line:84%
So I think he just
used the word, ich,

00:10:03.160 --> 00:10:04.930 align:middle line:90%
which is a German word.

00:10:04.930 --> 00:10:06.665 align:middle line:84%
But when it was
translated in the--

00:10:06.665 --> 00:10:08.040 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not a
great scholar, so I

00:10:08.040 --> 00:10:10.440 align:middle line:84%
might have this
completely wrong.

00:10:10.440 --> 00:10:14.030 align:middle line:84%
But what I've heard is that
it was Freud's translator

00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:16.740 align:middle line:84%
translating Freud to
English in the 1950s

00:10:16.740 --> 00:10:19.370 align:middle line:84%
after the war who
tried to translate

00:10:19.370 --> 00:10:23.100 align:middle line:84%
this word for individualization,
and he called it ego.

00:10:23.100 --> 00:10:25.510 align:middle line:90%
So there was ego, super ego, id.

00:10:25.510 --> 00:10:27.610 align:middle line:84%
So people now
often refer to that

00:10:27.610 --> 00:10:30.330 align:middle line:84%
like it's a thing, like you
got to get rid of your ego.

00:10:30.330 --> 00:10:32.207 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my ego made me do it.

00:10:32.207 --> 00:10:33.790 align:middle line:84%
I've got to get rid
of my ego, to work

00:10:33.790 --> 00:10:35.610 align:middle line:90%
on my ego likes it's a thing.

00:10:35.610 --> 00:10:37.214 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Like it's
a physical thing.

00:10:37.214 --> 00:10:39.130 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: But you can't
find a thing, you see.

00:10:39.130 --> 00:10:41.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, though
the ego can show up

00:10:41.820 --> 00:10:44.810 align:middle line:84%
in ways that feel
that they're solid.

00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:47.565 align:middle line:90%
Like rudeness or gregarity.

00:10:47.565 --> 00:10:48.190 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:10:48.190 --> 00:10:48.790 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:10:48.790 --> 00:10:51.659 align:middle line:84%
But rudeness is a function,
you see, it's not a thing.

00:10:51.659 --> 00:10:53.575 align:middle line:84%
Now, in the same way,
if I took a flashlight--

00:10:53.575 --> 00:10:56.300 align:middle line:84%
if it was dark in here
and I took a flashlight

00:10:56.300 --> 00:10:58.670 align:middle line:84%
and went like that,
you'd be tempted

00:10:58.670 --> 00:10:59.820 align:middle line:90%
to say there is a circle.

00:10:59.820 --> 00:11:00.404 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:11:00.404 --> 00:11:02.736 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: But there is no
circle, it's just a flashlight

00:11:02.736 --> 00:11:03.335 align:middle line:90%
going around.

00:11:03.335 --> 00:11:04.330 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:11:04.330 --> 00:11:08.790 align:middle line:84%
So in the same way, yes,
there is egoic behavior,

00:11:08.790 --> 00:11:09.820 align:middle line:90%
but that's a movement.

00:11:09.820 --> 00:11:11.840 align:middle line:90%
That's a movement in a medium.

00:11:11.840 --> 00:11:14.220 align:middle line:84%
And the moment the
movement stops, it's gone.

00:11:14.220 --> 00:11:15.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So behavior
is not solid.

00:11:15.770 --> 00:11:16.520 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Exactly.

00:11:16.520 --> 00:11:17.030 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:17.030 --> 00:11:19.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It could create
things like hurt feelings,

00:11:19.270 --> 00:11:20.600 align:middle line:90%
but those aren't solid either.

00:11:20.600 --> 00:11:21.490 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Right.

00:11:21.490 --> 00:11:25.640 align:middle line:84%
So in this moment-- in any
moment-- that we actually

00:11:25.640 --> 00:11:29.030 align:middle line:84%
wake up and pay
attention to what's real,

00:11:29.030 --> 00:11:32.230 align:middle line:84%
all of those things disappear--
the mind, the ego, the past,

00:11:32.230 --> 00:11:35.890 align:middle line:84%
the future-- all of it's
gone and there is just this.

00:11:35.890 --> 00:11:36.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:11:36.530 --> 00:11:38.260 align:middle line:90%
I have to go further with this.

00:11:38.260 --> 00:11:38.760 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:11:38.760 --> 00:11:41.450 align:middle line:90%


00:11:41.450 --> 00:11:44.550 align:middle line:84%
So take for instance
a bully, and the bully

00:11:44.550 --> 00:11:49.680 align:middle line:84%
is bullying someone and they
physically beat up on somebody.

00:11:49.680 --> 00:11:52.170 align:middle line:90%
That's a physical manifestation.

00:11:52.170 --> 00:11:53.520 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: It's a behavior.

00:11:53.520 --> 00:11:58.750 align:middle line:84%
If you were to do a
surgery on the person we're

00:11:58.750 --> 00:12:00.970 align:middle line:84%
calling a bully,
do a surgery, you

00:12:00.970 --> 00:12:03.010 align:middle line:90%
wouldn't find any bullyness.

00:12:03.010 --> 00:12:07.290 align:middle line:84%
It's just behavior-- a repeated
habitual behavior pattern.

00:12:07.290 --> 00:12:10.080 align:middle line:84%
Repeated habitual
behavior patterns

00:12:10.080 --> 00:12:15.020 align:middle line:84%
happen when we act
according to conditioning.

00:12:15.020 --> 00:12:17.100 align:middle line:84%
But as soon as we
have a moment, just

00:12:17.100 --> 00:12:21.310 align:middle line:84%
a taste of what
is actually here,

00:12:21.310 --> 00:12:25.930 align:middle line:84%
which is consciousness
experiencing this,

00:12:25.930 --> 00:12:27.175 align:middle line:90%
we break those patterns.

00:12:27.175 --> 00:12:29.400 align:middle line:90%
We interrupt those patterns.

00:12:29.400 --> 00:12:31.575 align:middle line:84%
Now, you-- maybe this
has happened for you.

00:12:31.575 --> 00:12:32.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:12:32.190 --> 00:12:34.890 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: I can remember you
mentioned a bully at school.

00:12:34.890 --> 00:12:40.030 align:middle line:84%
I can remember people who, when
I went to school with them,

00:12:40.030 --> 00:12:43.350 align:middle line:84%
were really-- were bullies, were
really unpleasant characters.

00:12:43.350 --> 00:12:44.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of course.

00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:46.364 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: And a few of them
I've met in later life.

00:12:46.364 --> 00:12:49.380 align:middle line:84%
And they've become the sweetest,
most caring, most kind, most

00:12:49.380 --> 00:12:50.760 align:middle line:90%
philanthropic people.

00:12:50.760 --> 00:12:53.330 align:middle line:84%
So then you could ask, well,
where did the bullyness go?

00:12:53.330 --> 00:12:54.940 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't surgically removed.

00:12:54.940 --> 00:12:57.570 align:middle line:84%
It was just a behavior
pattern changed.

00:12:57.570 --> 00:12:59.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that space
that you talk about,

00:12:59.920 --> 00:13:01.645 align:middle line:84%
that the hand
reached back and it

00:13:01.645 --> 00:13:04.910 align:middle line:84%
was infinite the
amount of space.

00:13:04.910 --> 00:13:08.180 align:middle line:84%
Did you ever go
back to the teacher

00:13:08.180 --> 00:13:12.370 align:middle line:84%
and tell him that you've
found what he's talking about?

00:13:12.370 --> 00:13:13.071 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yes.

00:13:13.071 --> 00:13:13.570 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:13:13.570 --> 00:13:14.090 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:13:14.090 --> 00:13:15.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What did he say?

00:13:15.280 --> 00:13:16.920 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Well,
since you asked I'll

00:13:16.920 --> 00:13:18.590 align:middle line:90%
tell you exactly what happened.

00:13:18.590 --> 00:13:21.190 align:middle line:84%
I actually-- That
moment of the laughing

00:13:21.190 --> 00:13:22.830 align:middle line:90%
happened early in the morning.

00:13:22.830 --> 00:13:23.830 align:middle line:90%
So then I had breakfast.

00:13:23.830 --> 00:13:25.980 align:middle line:84%
It was about the best
breakfast I've ever had.

00:13:25.980 --> 00:13:28.380 align:middle line:90%
Everything tasted fantastic.

00:13:28.380 --> 00:13:30.330 align:middle line:90%
The waiter was like an angel.

00:13:30.330 --> 00:13:32.545 align:middle line:84%
The world became
incredibly bright

00:13:32.545 --> 00:13:34.990 align:middle line:84%
and luminous and
enjoyable simply

00:13:34.990 --> 00:13:38.790 align:middle line:84%
because the pattern of endless
thought was interrupted.

00:13:38.790 --> 00:13:42.330 align:middle line:84%
And that is all that interferes
from this moment being

00:13:42.330 --> 00:13:43.210 align:middle line:90%
paradise.

00:13:43.210 --> 00:13:43.950 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:13:43.950 --> 00:13:46.690 align:middle line:84%
The only thing in the
way of this moment being

00:13:46.690 --> 00:13:49.200 align:middle line:90%
the best moment ever is this--

00:13:49.200 --> 00:13:50.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Suffering.

00:13:50.310 --> 00:13:52.060 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: --pattern
of automatic thinking.

00:13:52.060 --> 00:13:52.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:13:52.820 --> 00:13:55.450 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: So I went to see him.

00:13:55.450 --> 00:13:58.250 align:middle line:84%
And somebody asked a question--
some kind of question

00:13:58.250 --> 00:14:01.340 align:middle line:84%
like, why do we,
blah, blah, blah.

00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:03.520 align:middle line:84%
And he said to this
person, he said,

00:14:03.520 --> 00:14:05.770 align:middle line:84%
just a minute-- he was
very gruff-- just a minute,

00:14:05.770 --> 00:14:06.849 align:middle line:90%
he said, just a minute.

00:14:06.849 --> 00:14:09.390 align:middle line:84%
I have to finish my account with
this man, and pointed at me.

00:14:09.390 --> 00:14:12.090 align:middle line:84%
I have to finish my
account with this man.

00:14:12.090 --> 00:14:14.620 align:middle line:90%
So he called me forward.

00:14:14.620 --> 00:14:18.640 align:middle line:84%
And he called me forward I guess
to sit here, but I kind of just

00:14:18.640 --> 00:14:20.700 align:middle line:84%
kept going and ended
up kind of hugging him.

00:14:20.700 --> 00:14:24.010 align:middle line:84%
And I whispered in his ear,
I said the account's closed.

00:14:24.010 --> 00:14:25.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:14:25.480 --> 00:14:27.050 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: And he
knew what I meant.

00:14:27.050 --> 00:14:27.922 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:14:27.922 --> 00:14:29.630 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: The penny
had dropped, you see.

00:14:29.630 --> 00:14:30.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of course.

00:14:30.380 --> 00:14:33.310 align:middle line:90%
And it didn't ever turn back?

00:14:33.310 --> 00:14:34.810 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: It's not
really like that.

00:14:34.810 --> 00:14:39.130 align:middle line:84%
I think that that's-- that's
something we can talk about.

00:14:39.130 --> 00:14:41.825 align:middle line:84%
That's like a concept popular
in kind of spiritual mythology.

00:14:41.825 --> 00:14:42.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Please.

00:14:42.450 --> 00:14:42.740 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk.

00:14:42.740 --> 00:14:43.870 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: There's this
point of no return.

00:14:43.870 --> 00:14:45.161 align:middle line:90%
People call that enlightenment.

00:14:45.161 --> 00:14:49.120 align:middle line:84%
I think it's very misleading
to think of it that way.

00:14:49.120 --> 00:14:52.140 align:middle line:84%
It's, in the same
way, I mean, supposing

00:14:52.140 --> 00:14:55.610 align:middle line:84%
we're talking about
the sky, right?

00:14:55.610 --> 00:14:57.410 align:middle line:84%
And let's say you're
living in London

00:14:57.410 --> 00:14:58.720 align:middle line:90%
where there's a lot of clouds.

00:14:58.720 --> 00:15:01.610 align:middle line:84%
So you've kind of forgotten what
the sky is beyond the clouds.

00:15:01.610 --> 00:15:03.860 align:middle line:90%
You're only used to clouds.

00:15:03.860 --> 00:15:07.170 align:middle line:84%
And one day the clouds part
and I take you outside and say,

00:15:07.170 --> 00:15:08.290 align:middle line:90%
look, what do you see?

00:15:08.290 --> 00:15:09.465 align:middle line:90%
And you say, ah, it's blue.

00:15:09.465 --> 00:15:10.330 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Blue.

00:15:10.330 --> 00:15:11.250 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Maybe
it's even like one

00:15:11.250 --> 00:15:12.770 align:middle line:84%
of those three days
in the year in London

00:15:12.770 --> 00:15:14.930 align:middle line:84%
where there's no clouds
at all, and you go, wow,

00:15:14.930 --> 00:15:16.120 align:middle line:90%
it's completely blue.

00:15:16.120 --> 00:15:18.327 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:15:18.327 --> 00:15:20.160 align:middle line:84%
And then you could tell
a friend about this.

00:15:20.160 --> 00:15:23.150 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know, I went-- Arjuna
took me outside and pointed up

00:15:23.150 --> 00:15:24.750 align:middle line:90%
and it was blue, you see?

00:15:24.750 --> 00:15:27.660 align:middle line:84%
And then they might say,
well, but did it go back?

00:15:27.660 --> 00:15:30.490 align:middle line:84%
But it's not like that,
because once you recognize

00:15:30.490 --> 00:15:34.610 align:middle line:84%
the blueness of the sky, you
recognize the way things are,

00:15:34.610 --> 00:15:37.480 align:middle line:84%
and then it doesn't matter if
clouds come or they don't come.

00:15:37.480 --> 00:15:39.420 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It can't go back.

00:15:39.420 --> 00:15:40.850 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: You
realize that was not

00:15:40.850 --> 00:15:44.180 align:middle line:84%
a temporary change of
condition; you had an insight

00:15:44.180 --> 00:15:45.310 align:middle line:90%
into the way things are.

00:15:45.310 --> 00:15:50.370 align:middle line:84%
So if you're asking having
seen that the nature

00:15:50.370 --> 00:15:52.860 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness
is infinite, did it

00:15:52.860 --> 00:15:54.370 align:middle line:90%
ever stop being infinite again?

00:15:54.370 --> 00:15:54.890 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:15:54.890 --> 00:15:57.610 align:middle line:84%
The nature of consciousness
doesn't cease to be what it is.

00:15:57.610 --> 00:16:00.610 align:middle line:84%
But, of course,
you know what it's

00:16:00.610 --> 00:16:03.720 align:middle line:84%
like to have a relationship
and raise a child.

00:16:03.720 --> 00:16:05.400 align:middle line:90%
I've raised two kids.

00:16:05.400 --> 00:16:07.070 align:middle line:90%
And life is difficult sometimes.

00:16:07.070 --> 00:16:08.170 align:middle line:90%
Life is challenging.

00:16:08.170 --> 00:16:10.840 align:middle line:90%
You go through your stresses.

00:16:10.840 --> 00:16:13.480 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, it's just
the human experience.

00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:16.100 align:middle line:84%
We go through our
times of being more

00:16:16.100 --> 00:16:17.880 align:middle line:90%
caught up the less caught up.

00:16:17.880 --> 00:16:21.590 align:middle line:84%
But the realization
that all of this

00:16:21.590 --> 00:16:25.500 align:middle line:84%
is happening in the context
of infinite consciousness--

00:16:25.500 --> 00:16:27.200 align:middle line:90%
that can't be undone.

00:16:27.200 --> 00:16:28.950 align:middle line:84%
It's a recognition of
the way things are.

00:16:28.950 --> 00:16:29.549 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:16:29.549 --> 00:16:31.840 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's interesting,
because you mentioned earlier

00:16:31.840 --> 00:16:37.430 align:middle line:84%
about suffering and suffering
being the-- Buddhist philosophy

00:16:37.430 --> 00:16:41.780 align:middle line:84%
talks about suffering and
that the human being grapples

00:16:41.780 --> 00:16:44.930 align:middle line:84%
with the hero's journey
and goes through this phase

00:16:44.930 --> 00:16:46.260 align:middle line:90%
of suffering.

00:16:46.260 --> 00:16:49.980 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that we need to
have that level of suffering

00:16:49.980 --> 00:16:53.120 align:middle line:84%
before we can get to
this level of awakening?

00:16:53.120 --> 00:16:55.820 align:middle line:84%
Do you think we
need that contrast?

00:16:55.820 --> 00:16:57.520 align:middle line:90%
Is that why we create it?

00:16:57.520 --> 00:16:58.770 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: I think I needed it.

00:16:58.770 --> 00:16:59.814 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hm.

00:16:59.814 --> 00:17:00.730 align:middle line:90%
Certain ones of us do.

00:17:00.730 --> 00:17:02.485 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: I think I needed it.

00:17:02.485 --> 00:17:06.060 align:middle line:84%
It's very obvious
to me, looking back,

00:17:06.060 --> 00:17:08.800 align:middle line:84%
that the difficult
circumstances of my early life

00:17:08.800 --> 00:17:11.190 align:middle line:84%
were absolutely a blessing
and that I wouldn't

00:17:11.190 --> 00:17:15.599 align:middle line:84%
be enjoying everything
I have today

00:17:15.599 --> 00:17:17.500 align:middle line:84%
and able to give
everything I have today

00:17:17.500 --> 00:17:21.650 align:middle line:84%
were it not for that level
of suffering, because I coach

00:17:21.650 --> 00:17:22.750 align:middle line:90%
and I train coaches.

00:17:22.750 --> 00:17:23.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:17:23.430 --> 00:17:25.013 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: There is
nothing that anyone

00:17:25.013 --> 00:17:27.530 align:middle line:84%
can bring to me that
will phase me now.

00:17:27.530 --> 00:17:30.609 align:middle line:84%
However desperate people are
I go, I know what that's like.

00:17:30.609 --> 00:17:32.150 align:middle line:84%
And so it became a
blessing, you see.

00:17:32.150 --> 00:17:34.490 align:middle line:84%
It became something
that was of service.

00:17:34.490 --> 00:17:36.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So actually
let me talk to you

00:17:36.320 --> 00:17:38.536 align:middle line:84%
about the awakening
coaching that you do.

