what works for men

00:32:22.590 --> 00:32:26.280 align:middle line:84%
and what works for women
in terms of embodiment.

00:32:26.280 --> 00:32:29.190 align:middle line:84%
So if we're talking about
the tools that give you

00:32:29.190 --> 00:32:31.749 align:middle line:84%
the taste of awakening,
that's pretty much the same.

00:32:31.749 --> 00:32:33.290 align:middle line:84%
If we're talking
about the tools that

00:32:33.290 --> 00:32:35.970 align:middle line:84%
allow you to embody awakening,
that's very, very different

00:32:35.970 --> 00:32:39.660 align:middle line:84%
because embodiment
involves the balance

00:32:39.660 --> 00:32:41.560 align:middle line:84%
of the body and the
hormones that run

00:32:41.560 --> 00:32:44.190 align:middle line:84%
in a male and female body
are completely different.

00:32:44.190 --> 00:32:48.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You don't think that
that causes separateness?

00:32:48.220 --> 00:32:51.730 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Well, it's-- that
separateness has a beauty

00:32:51.730 --> 00:32:52.230 align:middle line:90%
to it.

00:32:52.230 --> 00:32:56.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean, attraction and
sexuality and falling in love

00:32:56.770 --> 00:32:59.530 align:middle line:84%
and all sort of things are a
function of that separateness.

00:32:59.530 --> 00:33:01.820 align:middle line:84%
I mean, not all
separateness is bad.

00:33:01.820 --> 00:33:03.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a great answer.

00:33:03.810 --> 00:33:07.080 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: There's
good separateness.

00:33:07.080 --> 00:33:09.370 align:middle line:84%
And that's actually a
little bit of the point.

00:33:09.370 --> 00:33:16.950 align:middle line:84%
That if we practice-- if we
use practices that are just

00:33:16.950 --> 00:33:23.550 align:middle line:84%
sort of calming, neutralizing
practices like, you know,

00:33:23.550 --> 00:33:26.220 align:middle line:90%
namaste, we are one.

00:33:26.220 --> 00:33:28.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's great
for staying really calm,

00:33:28.920 --> 00:33:31.424 align:middle line:84%
but there's actually by
now a considerable body

00:33:31.424 --> 00:33:33.090 align:middle line:84%
of scientific evidence
that demonstrates

00:33:33.090 --> 00:33:35.256 align:middle line:84%
that if you do this too
much, your genitals actually

00:33:35.256 --> 00:33:37.648 align:middle line:90%
wither and drop off.

00:33:37.648 --> 00:33:39.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There is not.

00:33:39.290 --> 00:33:40.790 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah,
Scientific American.

00:33:40.790 --> 00:33:42.748 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There is?

00:33:42.748 --> 00:33:44.730 align:middle line:90%
There is not!

00:33:44.730 --> 00:33:48.927 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Anyway, the thing is--
the thing is-- as you can see,

00:33:48.927 --> 00:33:50.760 align:middle line:84%
we don't want to get
too serious about this.

00:33:50.760 --> 00:33:52.980 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, the point is, you
see, that if you actually

00:33:52.980 --> 00:33:56.530 align:middle line:84%
want to live a passionate
life, which is not just

00:33:56.530 --> 00:33:59.139 align:middle line:84%
about sex and intimacy, but
it's about giving your gift

00:33:59.139 --> 00:33:59.680 align:middle line:90%
to the world.

00:33:59.680 --> 00:34:02.417 align:middle line:84%
If you want to be alive and
really live fully and not

00:34:02.417 --> 00:34:04.500 align:middle line:84%
just live in this kind of
trance of we're all one.

00:34:04.500 --> 00:34:07.360 align:middle line:84%
But if you want to really
participate in the world

00:34:07.360 --> 00:34:09.359 align:middle line:84%
and raise your children
beautifully and create

00:34:09.359 --> 00:34:12.620 align:middle line:84%
an incredible relationship
and do a great TV show and all

00:34:12.620 --> 00:34:14.760 align:middle line:84%
this stuff, if you
want to do all that,

00:34:14.760 --> 00:34:17.150 align:middle line:84%
then we don't just need
practices that dull you out

00:34:17.150 --> 00:34:19.300 align:middle line:90%
and make you really sort of--

00:34:19.300 --> 00:34:22.600 align:middle line:84%
You want practices that allow
you to live your passion.

00:34:22.600 --> 00:34:25.139 align:middle line:84%
Those practices are
different for men and women

00:34:25.139 --> 00:34:29.085 align:middle line:84%
because the way that we live
our energy is different.

00:34:29.085 --> 00:34:30.820 align:middle line:84%
Men, or masculine
energy, anyway,

00:34:30.820 --> 00:34:34.389 align:middle line:84%
tends to be more focused,
more goal oriented, more

00:34:34.389 --> 00:34:37.380 align:middle line:84%
to do with breaking through
barriers and going for a goal.

00:34:37.380 --> 00:34:39.370 align:middle line:84%
This is because of
testosterone, you see.

00:34:39.370 --> 00:34:42.739 align:middle line:84%
Women, on the other hand,
when they-- so, for a man--

00:34:42.739 --> 00:34:44.239 align:middle line:84%
now, this is
controversial stuff.

00:34:44.239 --> 00:34:44.780 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Very.

00:34:44.780 --> 00:34:46.650 align:middle line:84%
Because I find myself
that way a lot.

00:34:46.650 --> 00:34:48.401 align:middle line:84%
I'm goal oriented,
and I'm task oriented.

00:34:48.401 --> 00:34:49.900 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: We all
have both energies.

00:34:49.900 --> 00:34:52.429 align:middle line:84%
But it is useful to understand
that there are these two

00:34:52.429 --> 00:34:52.929 align:middle line:90%
