I mean, it's very,

00:34:59.680 --> 00:35:00.820 align:middle line:90%
very commonly understood.

00:35:00.820 --> 00:35:01.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It exists.

00:35:01.570 --> 00:35:01.770 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:35:01.770 --> 00:35:02.150 align:middle line:90%
It exists.

00:35:02.150 --> 00:35:02.250 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:35:02.250 --> 00:35:03.910 align:middle line:84%
So here's the thing--
we all have both.

00:35:03.910 --> 00:35:05.909 align:middle line:84%
Of course, I have feminine
energy and masculine.

00:35:05.909 --> 00:35:08.910 align:middle line:84%
You have masculine energy
as well as feminine, right?

00:35:08.910 --> 00:35:11.650 align:middle line:84%
But it's really great
to be able to understand

00:35:11.650 --> 00:35:14.420 align:middle line:84%
that there are these energies
and certain practices will

00:35:14.420 --> 00:35:17.010 align:middle line:84%
increase one and
certain practices

00:35:17.010 --> 00:35:18.199 align:middle line:90%
will increase another.

00:35:18.199 --> 00:35:18.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You got it.

00:35:18.990 --> 00:35:19.250 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:35:19.250 --> 00:35:20.791 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: And all
that's important is

00:35:20.791 --> 00:35:23.934 align:middle line:84%
that you have the freedom
to express yourself

00:35:23.934 --> 00:35:24.725 align:middle line:90%
without limitation.

00:35:24.725 --> 00:35:29.840 align:middle line:84%
Now, let me give you, if I may,
the most obvious example where

00:35:29.840 --> 00:35:31.110 align:middle line:90%
this is useful.

00:35:31.110 --> 00:35:31.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:35:31.650 --> 00:35:37.650 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: I've met women who
followed very masculine paths.

00:35:37.650 --> 00:35:39.967 align:middle line:84%
Now, one of my books came
out about 10 years ago,

00:35:39.967 --> 00:35:41.800 align:middle line:84%
it was called, "The
Translucent Revolution."

00:35:41.800 --> 00:35:44.910 align:middle line:84%
In that book there's a
story of Sherry Anderson,

00:35:44.910 --> 00:35:49.400 align:middle line:84%
who was a Zen monk--
a Zen abbot actually--

00:35:49.400 --> 00:35:50.750 align:middle line:90%
in Nova Scotia in Canada.

00:35:50.750 --> 00:35:52.640 align:middle line:90%
It was freezing cold.

00:35:52.640 --> 00:35:56.100 align:middle line:84%
She had actually a
Vietnamese Zen master.

00:35:56.100 --> 00:35:58.840 align:middle line:84%
Not quite sure how that
works with Vietnam and Japan.

00:35:58.840 --> 00:36:01.100 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, it was a
Vietnamese master.

00:36:01.100 --> 00:36:06.750 align:middle line:84%
And she was getting up at 4:00
AM to do Zazen meditation.

00:36:06.750 --> 00:36:08.420 align:middle line:90%
She was totally depressed.

00:36:08.420 --> 00:36:10.480 align:middle line:90%
She had a shaved head.

00:36:10.480 --> 00:36:14.300 align:middle line:84%
She felt like-- she
just felt lifeless.

00:36:14.300 --> 00:36:17.605 align:middle line:84%
And so she contacted
her teacher and said,

00:36:17.605 --> 00:36:19.069 align:middle line:90%
this is not working for me.

00:36:19.069 --> 00:36:20.110 align:middle line:90%
I feel totally depressed.

00:36:20.110 --> 00:36:22.570 align:middle line:84%
He said, get up
one hour earlier.

00:36:22.570 --> 00:36:27.180 align:middle line:84%
She was following Zazen, happens
to be a hyper masculine path.

00:36:27.180 --> 00:36:30.070 align:middle line:84%
It's perfectly good;
it's just very masculine.

00:36:30.070 --> 00:36:34.160 align:middle line:84%
So finally she got so
fed up, she gave up

00:36:34.160 --> 00:36:38.680 align:middle line:84%
her monk hood, abandoned her
robes, and she moved to Sedona,

00:36:38.680 --> 00:36:41.420 align:middle line:84%
Arizona, which happens to
be quite a feminine place,

00:36:41.420 --> 00:36:43.620 align:middle line:84%
grew her hair again
and started to dance.

00:36:43.620 --> 00:36:45.240 align:middle line:90%
She decided to do Sufi dancing.

00:36:45.240 --> 00:36:46.950 align:middle line:84%
She says within six
months she could

00:36:46.950 --> 00:36:51.437 align:middle line:84%
feel god flowing through
every cell of her body.

00:36:51.437 --> 00:36:53.270 align:middle line:84%
And then she went on
to write a book called,

00:36:53.270 --> 00:36:54.480 align:middle line:90%
"The Feminine Face of God."

00:36:54.480 --> 00:36:56.063 align:middle line:84%
And she developed a
whole thing around

00:36:56.063 --> 00:36:58.100 align:middle line:90%
feminine spiritual practice.

00:36:58.100 --> 00:37:00.520 align:middle line:84%
Now, she's a really
poignant example of somebody

00:37:00.520 --> 00:37:04.610 align:middle line:84%
who was simply practicing an
inappropriate thing for her.

00:37:04.610 --> 00:37:07.200 align:middle line:84%
That practice of Zazen would
be great for somebody else.

00:37:07.200 --> 00:37:08.190 align:middle line:90%
It'd be great for me.

00:37:08.190 --> 00:37:10.260 align:middle line:84%
I've got a very
masculine energy.

00:37:10.260 --> 00:37:12.570 align:middle line:84%
But for somebody with
a very feminine heart,

00:37:12.570 --> 00:37:14.110 align:middle line:90%
it was crippling her.

00:37:14.110 --> 00:37:17.620 align:middle line:84%
Now, I've seen-- in the course
of the time I've been teaching

00:37:17.620 --> 00:37:20.910 align:middle line:84%
this, I've seen so many women
who, in their innocence,

00:37:20.910 --> 00:37:24.860 align:middle line:84%
were really longing to know the
divine, to know that deep love,

00:37:24.860 --> 00:37:28.520 align:middle line:84%
but they were following a hyper
masculine approach, you see.

00:37:28.520 --> 00:37:31.010 align:middle line:84%
Now, it's all good,
and sometimes it

00:37:31.010 --> 00:37:33.900 align:middle line:84%
could be good for a woman to
use hyper masculine techniques

00:37:33.900 --> 00:37:36.740 align:middle line:84%
or masculine techniques, and
it's good for a man to dance.

00:37:36.740 --> 00:37:38.862 align:middle line:84%
But it's important
to understand there

00:37:38.862 --> 00:37:41.320 align:middle line:84%
are these different practices,
they have different effects,

00:37:41.320 --> 00:37:43.370 align:middle line:84%
and to use the right
practice at the right time

00:37:43.370 --> 00:37:44.800 align:middle line:90%
for the right person.

00:37:44.800 --> 00:37:46.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Very well said.

00:37:46.560 --> 00:37:48.720 align:middle line:84%
Yes, I've seen many
women in Hollywood

00:37:48.720 --> 00:37:53.700 align:middle line:84%
where there is a lot of
pre-defined positions

00:37:53.700 --> 00:37:56.070 align:middle line:84%
that had to do
with the male race.

00:37:56.070 --> 00:38:00.160 align:middle line:84%
And women that then get into
these executive positions

00:38:00.160 --> 00:38:02.850 align:middle line:84%
become very hard
and masculine when

00:38:02.850 --> 00:38:05.240 align:middle line:84%
they are in those
positions to compete.

00:38:05.240 --> 00:38:08.560 align:middle line:84%
And I've seen them
literally get sick

00:38:08.560 --> 00:38:10.650 align:middle line:84%
because they lose so
much of their femininity

00:38:10.650 --> 00:38:11.749 align:middle line:90%
and their female hormones.

00:38:11.749 --> 00:38:13.290 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Well,
here's the good news.

00:38:13.290 --> 00:38:16.330 align:middle line:84%
I'm not by any means suggesting
that women should not

00:38:16.330 --> 00:38:18.549 align:middle line:84%
be in positions of
responsibility or power.

00:38:18.549 --> 00:38:19.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Me neither.

00:38:19.340 --> 00:38:20.360 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: I'm not
saying that at all.

00:38:20.360 --> 00:38:22.272 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's a
different way of doing it.

00:38:22.272 --> 00:38:23.480 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: It's not even that.

00:38:23.480 --> 00:38:24.355 align:middle line:90%
Here's the good news.

00:38:24.355 --> 00:38:28.140 align:middle line:84%
You only need a tiny bit
of conscious practice

00:38:28.140 --> 00:38:31.491 align:middle line:84%
to balance hours of
other activities.

00:38:31.491 --> 00:38:32.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Good news.

00:38:32.240 --> 00:38:32.864 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:38:32.864 --> 00:38:35.755 align:middle line:84%
So this is the way that I
work with women clients who

00:38:35.755 --> 00:38:37.290 align:middle line:90%
come to me for coaching.

00:38:37.290 --> 00:38:39.162 align:middle line:84%
I've worked with
a woman who was--

00:38:39.162 --> 00:38:41.370 align:middle line:84%
I can't say which city
because it would be, you know,

00:38:41.370 --> 00:38:44.220 align:middle line:84%
but she was in a
big city in the US.

00:38:44.220 --> 00:38:47.700 align:middle line:84%
She was the coordinator
of all the judges.

00:38:47.700 --> 00:38:49.370 align:middle line:84%
So there were all
the judges, all men,

00:38:49.370 --> 00:38:51.220 align:middle line:84%
and she was the one
who had to keep them

00:38:51.220 --> 00:38:54.550 align:middle line:90%
all in tune with each other.

00:38:54.550 --> 00:39:01.110 align:middle line:84%
Well, she tried to do that by
exuding very masculine energy.

00:39:01.110 --> 00:39:05.720 align:middle line:84%
Well, of course, faced with
all these men being judges,

00:39:05.720 --> 00:39:08.220 align:middle line:84%
she never could do
the masculine thing

00:39:08.220 --> 00:39:10.640 align:middle line:90%
quite as well as they did.

00:39:10.640 --> 00:39:12.140 align:middle line:84%
So I said to her,
look, all you need

00:39:12.140 --> 00:39:14.160 align:middle line:84%
is a little bit of
feminine practice

00:39:14.160 --> 00:39:15.570 align:middle line:90%
to balance out all the day.

00:39:15.570 --> 00:39:17.820 align:middle line:84%
And I've done this
with executives,

00:39:17.820 --> 00:39:20.330 align:middle line:84%
with police, with
all kinds of things.

00:39:20.330 --> 00:39:23.040 align:middle line:84%
All you need--
this is a takeaway

00:39:23.040 --> 00:39:24.631 align:middle line:90%
from this conversation.

00:39:24.631 --> 00:39:26.130 align:middle line:84%
This is all that a
woman needs to do

00:39:26.130 --> 00:39:27.590 align:middle line:90%
who's in an executive position.

00:39:27.590 --> 00:39:29.450 align:middle line:84%
When she comes home
in the evening,

00:39:29.450 --> 00:39:31.000 align:middle line:84%
takes everything
off-- the jewelry,

00:39:31.000 --> 00:39:34.300 align:middle line:84%
everything-- has a shower
to wash it all away.

00:39:34.300 --> 00:39:36.350 align:middle line:84%
And then, funnily enough,
after the shower--

00:39:36.350 --> 00:39:38.850 align:middle line:84%
it may be overdoing it a bit
with the water-- you-- then you

00:39:38.850 --> 00:39:41.600 align:middle line:84%
have a bath, all righ,
with oils and everything.

00:39:41.600 --> 00:39:44.252 align:middle line:84%
Soak in a bath, right,
with maybe some candles.

00:39:44.252 --> 00:39:45.960 align:middle line:84%
Come out of the bath,
put nice-- and then

00:39:45.960 --> 00:39:48.470 align:middle line:84%
you massage nice
creams into the body.

00:39:48.470 --> 00:39:52.260 align:middle line:84%
This is all bringing up
oxytocin in the body.

00:39:52.260 --> 00:39:54.000 align:middle line:84%
Put on completely
different clothing,

00:39:54.000 --> 00:39:56.290 align:middle line:90%
like flowing silk clothing.

00:39:56.290 --> 00:39:59.870 align:middle line:84%
Light candles, some nice music,
Sarah McLaughlin or something.

00:39:59.870 --> 00:40:04.110 align:middle line:84%
An hour of that will completely
neutralize an entire day

00:40:04.110 --> 00:40:08.090 align:middle line:84%
of working in the most
masculine environment.

00:40:08.090 --> 00:40:10.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then how do you
get back into the masculine?

00:40:10.800 --> 00:40:11.980 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: You don't have
to worry about that.

00:40:11.980 --> 00:40:12.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:40:12.300 --> 00:40:13.100 align:middle line:90%
That definitely happens.

00:40:13.100 --> 00:40:13.360 align:middle line:90%
That's beautiful.

00:40:13.360 --> 00:40:15.360 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: But the same
thing for a man, you see.

00:40:15.360 --> 00:40:17.180 align:middle line:84%
You might have a
man who has been

00:40:17.180 --> 00:40:19.640 align:middle line:84%
in a very kind of
chaotic environment

00:40:19.640 --> 00:40:21.850 align:middle line:84%
where there's a lot of
things flying at him.

00:40:21.850 --> 00:40:26.100 align:middle line:84%
Like for me for many years
I was raising my kids alone

00:40:26.100 --> 00:40:27.390 align:middle line:90%
between marriages.

00:40:27.390 --> 00:40:29.740 align:middle line:84%
I had a period where
I was a single dad,

00:40:29.740 --> 00:40:31.990 align:middle line:84%
and, you know, I was doing
the shopping, the cleaning,

00:40:31.990 --> 00:40:32.536 align:middle line:90%
and cooking.

00:40:32.536 --> 00:40:35.160 align:middle line:90%


00:40:35.160 --> 00:40:37.017 align:middle line:84%
And men, generally
speaking-- this

00:40:37.017 --> 00:40:38.850 align:middle line:84%
ought to do with gender
difference-- because

00:40:38.850 --> 00:40:40.590 align:middle line:84%
of hormones, men are
not nearly as good

00:40:40.590 --> 00:40:43.030 align:middle line:90%
at multitasking as women are.

00:40:43.030 --> 00:40:46.260 align:middle line:84%
So men get much
more-- so for a man,

00:40:46.260 --> 00:40:49.520 align:middle line:84%
you only need to sit or
do chikun or something

00:40:49.520 --> 00:40:52.471 align:middle line:84%
for a few minutes of centering
and it brings you back.

00:40:52.471 --> 00:40:53.970 align:middle line:84%
And you don't have
to do it all day.

00:40:53.970 --> 00:40:56.170 align:middle line:90%
That's the point about practice.

00:40:56.170 --> 00:40:59.269 align:middle line:84%
You practice meditation
or dance or yoga,

00:40:59.269 --> 00:41:00.810 align:middle line:84%
you don't have to
do it all the time.

00:41:00.810 --> 00:41:02.976 align:middle line:84%
A little bit is enough to
bring you back to balance.

00:41:02.976 --> 00:41:04.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Can recenter.

00:41:04.060 --> 00:41:07.910 align:middle line:84%
Well, regardless of gender,
everyone has a deep longing.

00:41:07.910 --> 00:41:11.470 align:middle line:84%
And this next clip here is
about discovering your deepest

00:41:11.470 --> 00:41:12.050 align:middle line:90%
longing.

00:41:12.050 --> 00:41:13.980 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:41:13.980 --> 00:41:16.730 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: What is
your deepest longing?

00:41:16.730 --> 00:41:19.280 align:middle line:90%


00:41:19.280 --> 00:41:25.230 align:middle line:84%
I've asked that question or
facilitated that question being

00:41:25.230 --> 00:41:27.840 align:middle line:84%
asked in groups with
thousands and thousands

00:41:27.840 --> 00:41:29.330 align:middle line:90%
and thousands of people.

00:41:29.330 --> 00:41:32.140 align:middle line:84%
And I've come to
a few observations

00:41:32.140 --> 00:41:35.090 align:middle line:84%
that I want to share with
you about that question.

00:41:35.090 --> 00:41:40.070 align:middle line:84%
The first observation is
it's not just the question

00:41:40.070 --> 00:41:43.190 align:middle line:84%
but the space from which
the question is asked

00:41:43.190 --> 00:41:44.910 align:middle line:90%
makes all the difference.

00:41:44.910 --> 00:41:47.280 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to do a really
quick demonstration of this

00:41:47.280 --> 00:41:49.270 align:middle line:90%
with Vicki.

00:41:49.270 --> 00:41:50.530 align:middle line:90%
I just volunteered Vicki.

00:41:50.530 --> 00:41:52.890 align:middle line:84%
So here's one way
to ask the question.

00:41:52.890 --> 00:41:54.550 align:middle line:90%
Something like this.

00:41:54.550 --> 00:41:55.840 align:middle line:90%
Hey, Vicki, you're from?

00:41:55.840 --> 00:41:57.340 align:middle line:90%
>>AUDIENCE: Ventura.

00:41:57.340 --> 00:41:58.180 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Ventura.

00:41:58.180 --> 00:41:58.950 align:middle line:90%
Very nice.

00:41:58.950 --> 00:42:01.010 align:middle line:90%
I've been to Ventura.

00:42:01.010 --> 00:42:03.204 align:middle line:84%
There's some cool people
living in Ventura.

00:42:03.204 --> 00:42:04.870 align:middle line:84%
Now, tell me Vicki,
I'm curious to know.

00:42:04.870 --> 00:42:06.078 align:middle line:90%
What is your deepest longing?

00:42:06.078 --> 00:42:08.017 align:middle line:90%


00:42:08.017 --> 00:42:09.350 align:middle line:90%
>>AUDIENCE: You want the answer?

00:42:09.350 --> 00:42:09.974 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:42:09.974 --> 00:42:13.010 align:middle line:84%
Tell me your deepest
longing, Vicki.

00:42:13.010 --> 00:42:14.280 align:middle line:90%
>>AUDIENCE: Grace and ease.

00:42:14.280 --> 00:42:15.630 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Grace and ease.

00:42:15.630 --> 00:42:16.390 align:middle line:90%
Fantastic.

00:42:16.390 --> 00:42:18.850 align:middle line:84%
Isn't there a TV show
called grace and ease.

00:42:18.850 --> 00:42:20.950 align:middle line:84%
No, maybe that's
"Will and Grace."

00:42:20.950 --> 00:42:22.010 align:middle line:90%
Great answer, Vicki.

00:42:22.010 --> 00:42:22.510 align:middle line:90%
Wonderful.

00:42:22.510 --> 00:42:24.718 align:middle line:84%
Give a round of applause to
Vicki for grace and ease.

00:42:24.718 --> 00:42:30.490 align:middle line:84%
Now, wait, wait, wait, tell me
your deepest longing, Vicki.

00:42:30.490 --> 00:42:31.100 align:middle line:90%
Go ahead.

00:42:31.100 --> 00:42:32.160 align:middle line:84%
>>AUDIENCE: Are
we starting again?

00:42:32.160 --> 00:42:32.460 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:42:32.460 --> 00:42:34.334 align:middle line:84%
Just tell me your deepest
longing, would you?

00:42:34.334 --> 00:42:35.550 align:middle line:90%
>>AUDIENCE: Grace and ease.

00:42:35.550 --> 00:42:36.080 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Grace and ease.

00:42:36.080 --> 00:42:37.871 align:middle line:84%
Let me just see if
there's an app for that.

00:42:37.871 --> 00:42:39.070 align:middle line:90%
Let's see, Grace-- OK.

00:42:39.070 --> 00:42:41.100 align:middle line:84%
So that's one way to
ask the question, right,

00:42:41.100 --> 00:42:44.320 align:middle line:84%
which obviously I exaggerated
it for dramatic purposes.

00:42:44.320 --> 00:42:47.540 align:middle line:84%
But to ask it in a
kind of high energy

00:42:47.540 --> 00:42:48.790 align:middle line:90%
but slightly distracted state.

00:42:48.790 --> 00:42:51.090 align:middle line:90%
Now let me ask you again.

00:42:51.090 --> 00:42:53.340 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:42:53.340 --> 00:42:58.402 align:middle line:84%
Hey, Vicki, what's
your deepest longing?

00:42:58.402 --> 00:43:04.865 align:middle line:90%


00:43:04.865 --> 00:43:05.740 align:middle line:90%
>>AUDIENCE: The same.

00:43:05.740 --> 00:43:07.100 align:middle line:90%
Grace and ease.

00:43:07.100 --> 00:43:09.980 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Mm-hm.

00:43:09.980 --> 00:43:11.990 align:middle line:90%
And what's even deeper?

00:43:11.990 --> 00:43:13.834 align:middle line:90%
What's your deepest longing?

00:43:13.834 --> 00:43:15.820 align:middle line:90%
>>AUDIENCE: Um, peace.

00:43:15.820 --> 00:43:18.530 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Peace.

00:43:18.530 --> 00:43:22.480 align:middle line:90%
So quick contrast.

00:43:22.480 --> 00:43:25.110 align:middle line:84%
The answers you're going
to get to that question

00:43:25.110 --> 00:43:29.160 align:middle line:84%
vary tremendously on
the degree of presence

00:43:29.160 --> 00:43:32.460 align:middle line:90%
which we bring as a coach.

00:43:32.460 --> 00:43:34.560 align:middle line:84%
We could obviously elaborate
a lot more on that,

00:43:34.560 --> 00:43:37.510 align:middle line:84%
but I've got 15 minutes
and the clock's whirring,

00:43:37.510 --> 00:43:41.080 align:middle line:84%
so let me tell you the
second observation.

00:43:41.080 --> 00:43:45.430 align:middle line:84%
When we work with this question,
asking people to go deeper,

00:43:45.430 --> 00:43:49.860 align:middle line:84%
I've noticed that
longing works in layers.

00:43:49.860 --> 00:43:52.340 align:middle line:84%
And very often the
first answer people

00:43:52.340 --> 00:43:56.610 align:middle line:84%
give you may not actually
be their deepest answer.

00:43:56.610 --> 00:43:58.245 align:middle line:90%
Not that it's the wrong answer.

00:43:58.245 --> 00:44:00.816 align:middle line:84%
It might be-- in fact, it might
even be the correct answer,

00:44:00.816 --> 00:44:02.940 align:middle line:84%
but it's more like the
words and the feeling of it.

00:44:02.940 --> 00:44:04.670 align:middle line:84%
Do you know the
difference with that?

00:44:04.670 --> 00:44:06.860 align:middle line:84%
Somebody could
say-- you could ask,

00:44:06.860 --> 00:44:08.960 align:middle line:90%
what's your deepest longing?

00:44:08.960 --> 00:44:10.300 align:middle line:90%
Oneness with all things.

00:44:10.300 --> 00:44:12.510 align:middle line:84%
But it's somehow you can
feel that they're just

00:44:12.510 --> 00:44:16.200 align:middle line:84%
quoting Eckhart Tolle
rather than really

00:44:16.200 --> 00:44:18.800 align:middle line:90%
feeling the longing itself.

00:44:18.800 --> 00:44:20.360 align:middle line:90%
Longing goes in layers.

00:44:20.360 --> 00:44:23.980 align:middle line:84%
And what I've noticed is if
you can help someone as a coach

00:44:23.980 --> 00:44:27.080 align:middle line:84%
to shift from one layer
of longing to another,

00:44:27.080 --> 00:44:32.750 align:middle line:84%
the deeper layer will actually
nourish the initial layer.

00:44:32.750 --> 00:44:34.000 align:middle line:90%
You see what I mean?

00:44:34.000 --> 00:44:35.219 align:middle line:90%
So here's an example.

00:44:35.219 --> 00:44:37.260 align:middle line:84%
We might start with, what's
your deepest longing?

00:44:37.260 --> 00:44:41.300 align:middle line:84%
To have a $2 million a
year income, a great house,

00:44:41.300 --> 00:44:42.600 align:middle line:90%
and a Ferrari.

00:44:42.600 --> 00:44:43.370 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:44:43.370 --> 00:44:46.390 align:middle line:90%
What's your deepest longing?

00:44:46.390 --> 00:44:49.150 align:middle line:90%
To make a difference.

00:44:49.150 --> 00:44:50.280 align:middle line:90%
To serve people.

00:44:50.280 --> 00:44:52.330 align:middle line:90%
To contribute.

00:44:52.330 --> 00:44:53.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, you probably
know-- I'm sure you

00:44:53.990 --> 00:44:56.270 align:middle line:84%
know as coaches, if
you can serve someone

00:44:56.270 --> 00:44:58.600 align:middle line:84%
to make a contribution,
it's probably

00:44:58.600 --> 00:45:01.850 align:middle line:84%
going to give them a
comfortable lifestyle.

00:45:01.850 --> 00:45:04.030 align:middle line:84%
Going after the lifestyle
is not necessarily

00:45:04.030 --> 00:45:05.620 align:middle line:84%
going to give them
a sense of service.

00:45:05.620 --> 00:45:06.750 align:middle line:90%
You see the point?

00:45:06.750 --> 00:45:08.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So I love
how you bring what

00:45:08.460 --> 00:45:10.750 align:middle line:84%
you talk about into
practical terms

00:45:10.750 --> 00:45:15.060 align:middle line:84%
because ultimately you're
residing in the US now

00:45:15.060 --> 00:45:17.680 align:middle line:84%
and you are-- part
of your destiny

00:45:17.680 --> 00:45:20.720 align:middle line:84%
is to bring these teachings
from your vast experiences

00:45:20.720 --> 00:45:22.380 align:middle line:90%
to a practical level.

00:45:22.380 --> 00:45:26.300 align:middle line:84%
And even though the Gaiam
audience is international,

00:45:26.300 --> 00:45:28.680 align:middle line:84%
it appeals to every
single person.

00:45:28.680 --> 00:45:31.620 align:middle line:84%
Now you recently did
a talk at Google.

00:45:31.620 --> 00:45:33.280 align:middle line:84%
And why did they
bring you in there--

00:45:33.280 --> 00:45:36.235 align:middle line:84%
I was just curious-- to a group
of software engineers, yes?

00:45:36.235 --> 00:45:36.860 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:45:36.860 --> 00:45:39.330 align:middle line:84%
Well, Google is a great
company like that.

00:45:39.330 --> 00:45:44.920 align:middle line:84%
Google is, I think,
the pioneer, globally,

00:45:44.920 --> 00:45:50.010 align:middle line:84%
at really making an attempt
to fundamentally transform

00:45:50.010 --> 00:45:51.840 align:middle line:90%
corporate culture.

00:45:51.840 --> 00:46:02.370 align:middle line:84%
Because it's-- By now it's a
warn out idiom that people say

00:46:02.370 --> 00:46:03.870 align:middle line:90%
thank God it's Friday.

00:46:03.870 --> 00:46:04.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:46:04.690 --> 00:46:06.690 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: It's kind of
commonly understood maxim

00:46:06.690 --> 00:46:08.390 align:middle line:84%
that people don't
like going to work.

00:46:08.390 --> 00:46:09.640 align:middle line:90%
But it's completely illogical.

00:46:09.640 --> 00:46:12.230 align:middle line:84%
I mean, since you spend
most of your time there,

00:46:12.230 --> 00:46:15.200 align:middle line:84%
it would really make
sense that we look forward

00:46:15.200 --> 00:46:16.220 align:middle line:90%
to going to work.

00:46:16.220 --> 00:46:17.510 align:middle line:90%
Because I do.

00:46:17.510 --> 00:46:20.170 align:middle line:84%
I don't ever leave work
because I enjoy it so much.

00:46:20.170 --> 00:46:25.250 align:middle line:84%
So Google is really
pioneering what's

00:46:25.250 --> 00:46:30.800 align:middle line:84%
it going to take to create
a corporate culture that

00:46:30.800 --> 00:46:32.760 align:middle line:84%
gets the job done
but that actually

00:46:32.760 --> 00:46:35.220 align:middle line:84%
gets people inspired
and passionate.

00:46:35.220 --> 00:46:37.669 align:middle line:84%
And it's a work in
progress, of course.

00:46:37.669 --> 00:46:38.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's great.

00:46:38.460 --> 00:46:40.460 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: So they've
installed meditation rooms.

00:46:40.460 --> 00:46:44.510 align:middle line:84%
They've got a slide instead of
stairs in one of the buildings.

00:46:44.510 --> 00:46:46.840 align:middle line:84%
They've done everything they
can to make it more fun.

00:46:46.840 --> 00:46:48.940 align:middle line:84%
But, of course,
what's really required

00:46:48.940 --> 00:46:52.090 align:middle line:84%
is not just external
change but to really help

00:46:52.090 --> 00:46:53.880 align:middle line:84%
people to shift
their consciousness.

00:46:53.880 --> 00:46:56.659 align:middle line:84%
So they invite all
sorts of experts

00:46:56.659 --> 00:46:57.950 align:middle line:90%
in who have something to offer.

00:46:57.950 --> 00:47:00.780 align:middle line:84%
They have a program
called Google Pause.

00:47:00.780 --> 00:47:03.910 align:middle line:90%
So I was speaking in that vein.

00:47:03.910 --> 00:47:06.400 align:middle line:84%
And I was very, very
grateful for the reception.

00:47:06.400 --> 00:47:08.504 align:middle line:84%
People were very,
very open there.

00:47:08.504 --> 00:47:10.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you were
talking about inspiring

00:47:10.420 --> 00:47:11.546 align:middle line:90%
your creative genius, yeah?

00:47:11.546 --> 00:47:12.170 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Yeah.

00:47:12.170 --> 00:47:12.820 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:47:12.820 --> 00:47:15.115 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's the thing,
you see, that awakening--

00:47:15.115 --> 00:47:18.970 align:middle line:84%
when we talk about
awakening, it has really

00:47:18.970 --> 00:47:22.960 align:middle line:84%
being fostered in
oriental cultures, which

00:47:22.960 --> 00:47:25.580 align:middle line:84%
tend to be more
inward and reclusive.

00:47:25.580 --> 00:47:28.880 align:middle line:84%
So it's hot there-- India,
especially the south of India,

00:47:28.880 --> 00:47:29.930 align:middle line:90%
it's very hot.

00:47:29.930 --> 00:47:31.700 align:middle line:90%
Too hot to do very much.

00:47:31.700 --> 00:47:32.862 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:47:32.862 --> 00:47:33.362 align:middle line:90%
Very still.

00:47:33.362 --> 00:47:35.695 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: You have to spend
a lot of time keeping still.

00:47:35.695 --> 00:47:37.570 align:middle line:84%
But we don't live
in such a hot place,

00:47:37.570 --> 00:47:39.810 align:middle line:90%
so we're not quite so reclusive.

00:47:39.810 --> 00:47:42.100 align:middle line:84%
And for you and me
and everybody we know,

00:47:42.100 --> 00:47:44.640 align:middle line:84%
our lives are about
creating stuff.

00:47:44.640 --> 00:47:46.710 align:middle line:84%
So we have children
and we have a house,

00:47:46.710 --> 00:47:49.830 align:middle line:84%
make the house beautiful,
and then you do what you can

00:47:49.830 --> 00:47:51.880 align:middle line:84%
for the environment
and for transforming

00:47:51.880 --> 00:47:53.580 align:middle line:90%
the economy and politics.

00:47:53.580 --> 00:47:55.860 align:middle line:90%
Your life is about contribution.

00:47:55.860 --> 00:47:58.030 align:middle line:84%
So when-- I think
probably it would

00:47:58.030 --> 00:48:00.440 align:middle line:84%
be true for most of the
people listening to this,

00:48:00.440 --> 00:48:04.490 align:middle line:84%
just getting into a kind of
empty state and staying there,

00:48:04.490 --> 00:48:06.760 align:middle line:84%
that doesn't really
feel like a good use

00:48:06.760 --> 00:48:07.920 align:middle line:90%
of a life for most people.

00:48:07.920 --> 00:48:10.890 align:middle line:84%
We want to actually
manifest that.

00:48:10.890 --> 00:48:13.300 align:middle line:84%
So the good news
is that when you

00:48:13.300 --> 00:48:16.860 align:middle line:84%
tune into this infinite
consciousness, in one sense

00:48:16.860 --> 00:48:18.590 align:middle line:90%
it's empty.

00:48:18.590 --> 00:48:23.470 align:middle line:84%
From the perspective of
color and shape and movement

00:48:23.470 --> 00:48:25.088 align:middle line:90%
and sound, it is empty.

00:48:25.088 --> 00:48:28.510 align:middle line:90%


00:48:28.510 --> 00:48:33.780 align:middle line:84%
But in another way, it is
full of pure potentiality.

00:48:33.780 --> 00:48:35.600 align:middle line:90%
It is the source of all love.

00:48:35.600 --> 00:48:37.050 align:middle line:90%
Where does love come from?

00:48:37.050 --> 00:48:40.470 align:middle line:84%
You know, when we sit and
meet-- when friends sit and meet

00:48:40.470 --> 00:48:43.070 align:middle line:84%
and we look into each other's
eyes, we go, ah, yeah.

00:48:43.070 --> 00:48:43.620 align:middle line:90%
It's here.

00:48:43.620 --> 00:48:45.036 align:middle line:84%
Where does that
feeling come from?

00:48:45.036 --> 00:48:46.080 align:middle line:90%
It's not biological.

00:48:46.080 --> 00:48:49.440 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing in the
cells that can do that.

00:48:49.440 --> 00:48:52.730 align:middle line:84%
It's something-- it's that
infinite consciousness.

00:48:52.730 --> 00:48:55.210 align:middle line:84%
It is love itself,
but it is also

00:48:55.210 --> 00:48:58.790 align:middle line:90%
the source of every new idea.

00:48:58.790 --> 00:49:01.860 align:middle line:90%
Where do ideas come from?

00:49:01.860 --> 00:49:04.106 align:middle line:84%
You can regurgitate
things you've heard.

00:49:04.106 --> 00:49:05.980 align:middle line:84%
If you go to school and
you learn this thing,

00:49:05.980 --> 00:49:07.990 align:middle line:90%
you can repeat it for the exam.

00:49:07.990 --> 00:49:09.812 align:middle line:90%
That's coming from conditioning.

00:49:09.812 --> 00:49:11.270 align:middle line:84%
But if you read
something in a book

00:49:11.270 --> 00:49:13.310 align:middle line:84%
and reorganize it
and then come forth

00:49:13.310 --> 00:49:15.760 align:middle line:84%
with an original, new
idea, that does not

00:49:15.760 --> 00:49:18.140 align:middle line:84%
come from conditioning,
that comes from--

00:49:18.140 --> 00:49:19.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Inspiration.

00:49:19.510 --> 00:49:23.870 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: That comes from--
yeah, like the-- the dark hole,

00:49:23.870 --> 00:49:27.209 align:middle line:84%
you could say the black hole out
of which everything manifests.

00:49:27.209 --> 00:49:29.500 align:middle line:84%
If you've seen this new movie
about the life of Stephen

00:49:29.500 --> 00:49:31.541 align:middle line:84%
Hawking where he's-- it's
a very beautiful movie.

00:49:31.541 --> 00:49:34.384 align:middle line:84%
It's called "The
Theory of Everything."

00:49:34.384 --> 00:49:35.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, wonderful.

00:49:35.300 --> 00:49:37.383 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: And he's talking
in that movie about how

00:49:37.383 --> 00:49:39.179 align:middle line:84%
black holes are
incredibly compressed,

00:49:39.179 --> 00:49:41.845 align:middle line:84%
but they actually are the source
out of which everything arises,

00:49:41.845 --> 00:49:46.890 align:middle line:84%
you see, so that infinite space
which is formless, timeless,

00:49:46.890 --> 00:49:51.220 align:middle line:84%
which has no content, it's
out of that unmanifest source

00:49:51.220 --> 00:49:52.670 align:middle line:90%
that everything arises.

00:49:52.670 --> 00:49:55.850 align:middle line:90%
So we were talking earlier.

00:49:55.850 --> 00:50:00.570 align:middle line:84%
Every example of true
genius-- true genius

00:50:00.570 --> 00:50:03.400 align:middle line:84%
is not the capacity to
regurgitate what you've heard;

00:50:03.400 --> 00:50:07.440 align:middle line:84%
true genius is the capacity
to be a vehicle for something

00:50:07.440 --> 00:50:10.860 align:middle line:84%
to pass through you-- not
from you-- from a source that

00:50:10.860 --> 00:50:11.600 align:middle line:90%
is unknown.

00:50:11.600 --> 00:50:15.180 align:middle line:84%
So it's well known
that Albert Einstein,

00:50:15.180 --> 00:50:18.120 align:middle line:84%
he came up with a theory of
relativity in the bathtub.

00:50:18.120 --> 00:50:20.010 align:middle line:90%
He wasn't sitting, trying.

00:50:20.010 --> 00:50:21.880 align:middle line:90%
He was spacious.

00:50:21.880 --> 00:50:23.860 align:middle line:84%
Good friend of
ours, Jack Canfield

00:50:23.860 --> 00:50:25.630 align:middle line:84%
who has sold more
books in his field

00:50:25.630 --> 00:50:28.884 align:middle line:84%
than in history, where did
he come up with the title

00:50:28.884 --> 00:50:30.050 align:middle line:90%
"Chicken Soup for the Soul?"

00:50:30.050 --> 00:50:30.970 align:middle line:90%
He was meditating.

00:50:30.970 --> 00:50:32.170 align:middle line:90%
He was spacious.

00:50:32.170 --> 00:50:34.950 align:middle line:84%
And he saw this hand, "Chicken
Soup," and he had a thought,

00:50:34.950 --> 00:50:36.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to call
my book "Chicken Soup."

00:50:36.340 --> 00:50:37.881 align:middle line:84%
And the hand went
on, "for the Soul."

00:50:37.881 --> 00:50:38.580 align:middle line:90%
He went, oh.

00:50:38.580 --> 00:50:40.160 align:middle line:90%
It came to him.

00:50:40.160 --> 00:50:42.790 align:middle line:84%
Steve Jobs, we were talking
about Steve Jobs earlier, well,

00:50:42.790 --> 00:50:47.020 align:middle line:84%
most people know now Steve Jobs,
he started out experimenting

00:50:47.020 --> 00:50:50.206 align:middle line:84%
with all kinds of consciousness
changing methodologies.

00:50:50.206 --> 00:50:54.260 align:middle line:84%
And that opened his space
enough to bring forth

00:50:54.260 --> 00:50:57.450 align:middle line:84%
a whole revolution in the way
that we think about computers.

00:50:57.450 --> 00:51:00.380 align:middle line:84%
So every genius, everyone
who brings something

00:51:00.380 --> 00:51:02.330 align:middle line:84%
fresh that's never
been there before,

00:51:02.330 --> 00:51:04.030 align:middle line:84%
they have access
to the infinite.

00:51:04.030 --> 00:51:05.980 align:middle line:84%
And this is where
awakening-- it's

00:51:05.980 --> 00:51:08.490 align:middle line:84%
not just about escaping
the world at all--

00:51:08.490 --> 00:51:12.310 align:middle line:84%
it's about being connected to
the source in which brilliance

00:51:12.310 --> 00:51:13.360 align:middle line:90%
arises.

00:51:13.360 --> 00:51:14.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Beautiful.

00:51:14.210 --> 00:51:14.710 align:middle line:90%
Beautiful.

00:51:14.710 --> 00:51:18.270 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look at
Arjuna's talk at Google.

00:51:18.270 --> 00:51:19.757 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:51:19.757 --> 00:51:21.840 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: And that's really
been the question that

00:51:21.840 --> 00:51:26.900 align:middle line:84%
has governed my
entire adult life.

00:51:26.900 --> 00:51:29.770 align:middle line:84%
From being a student at
Cambridge University,

00:51:29.770 --> 00:51:33.290 align:middle line:84%
that was really what fascinated
me more than anything else.

00:51:33.290 --> 00:51:36.165 align:middle line:84%
What is it that allows
us-- Well, first

00:51:36.165 --> 00:51:37.540 align:middle line:84%
of all, what is
it that allows us

00:51:37.540 --> 00:51:39.670 align:middle line:84%
to live incredibly
fulfilled lives?

00:51:39.670 --> 00:51:43.000 align:middle line:84%
What is the key that allows
some people under almost

00:51:43.000 --> 00:51:46.880 align:middle line:84%
any circumstance to be
living a life of no regret?

00:51:46.880 --> 00:51:49.060 align:middle line:84%
To be living a life where
you are impassioned,

00:51:49.060 --> 00:51:52.660 align:middle line:84%
where you're on fire, where
you feel grateful easily.

00:51:52.660 --> 00:51:56.300 align:middle line:84%
And what is it that allows many
other people to be suffering,

00:51:56.300 --> 00:51:59.570 align:middle line:84%
not always for physical reasons,
but especially in our culture

00:51:59.570 --> 00:52:02.870 align:middle line:84%
people suffer more for
psychological reasons,

00:52:02.870 --> 00:52:05.480 align:middle line:84%
for attitudinal
reasons more than

00:52:05.480 --> 00:52:07.630 align:middle line:84%
because they don't
have enough food

00:52:07.630 --> 00:52:13.420 align:middle line:90%
or water or physical things.

00:52:13.420 --> 00:52:15.970 align:middle line:84%
Initially in this
investigation, I

00:52:15.970 --> 00:52:18.780 align:middle line:84%
thought that
ultimate fulfillment

00:52:18.780 --> 00:52:23.960 align:middle line:84%
was to do with spirituality
because a lot of the most

00:52:23.960 --> 00:52:27.720 align:middle line:84%
fulfilled people in our
culture have been mystics,

00:52:27.720 --> 00:52:31.880 align:middle line:84%
have been people who have
created spiritual traditions

00:52:31.880 --> 00:52:33.370 align:middle line:90%
or religions.

00:52:33.370 --> 00:52:35.060 align:middle line:84%
But actually, when
we investigate it

00:52:35.060 --> 00:52:37.590 align:middle line:84%
in an objective way,
it's not always true.

00:52:37.590 --> 00:52:40.340 align:middle line:84%
You can make your life
about spirituality,

00:52:40.340 --> 00:52:42.260 align:middle line:84%
you can make your
life about meditation;

00:52:42.260 --> 00:52:47.090 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't necessarily in a
reliable way to fulfillment.

00:52:47.090 --> 00:52:49.130 align:middle line:90%
So what else could it be?

00:52:49.130 --> 00:52:51.620 align:middle line:84%
Then I considered
maybe it's love.

00:52:51.620 --> 00:52:54.100 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's having
perfect relationships,

00:52:54.100 --> 00:52:58.450 align:middle line:84%
having the right spouse
and the right 2.35 children

00:52:58.450 --> 00:53:00.230 align:middle line:84%
and the right suburb
of the right city.

00:53:00.230 --> 00:53:03.040 align:middle line:84%
Maybe that's the
key to fulfillment.

00:53:03.040 --> 00:53:05.540 align:middle line:84%
We don't have so long to go
into all the possibilities--

00:53:05.540 --> 00:53:07.460 align:middle line:84%
and there are many
possible answers--

00:53:07.460 --> 00:53:11.280 align:middle line:84%
but what seems to hit
the nail every time

00:53:11.280 --> 00:53:15.290 align:middle line:84%
is to drop into the
frequency of genius.

00:53:15.290 --> 00:53:18.680 align:middle line:84%
When we fall into-- as
Rachel was speaking,

00:53:18.680 --> 00:53:21.930 align:middle line:84%
when we fall into a
flow where you know

00:53:21.930 --> 00:53:24.350 align:middle line:84%
you're doing the
right thing, you

00:53:24.350 --> 00:53:27.090 align:middle line:84%
know you're creating
the right thing,

00:53:27.090 --> 00:53:29.660 align:middle line:84%
you know that you're
contributing exactly what you

00:53:29.660 --> 00:53:33.300 align:middle line:84%
were born to contribute,
to contribute to all of us

00:53:33.300 --> 00:53:35.290 align:middle line:84%
moving forwards,
that, I would say,

00:53:35.290 --> 00:53:38.800 align:middle line:84%
whenever someone falls
into that frequency,

00:53:38.800 --> 00:53:42.490 align:middle line:84%
it's a reliable key to
a life of no regret--

00:53:42.490 --> 00:53:45.412 align:middle line:84%
to a life of
complete fulfillment.

00:53:45.412 --> 00:53:46.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The question
that's arising

00:53:46.870 --> 00:53:49.100 align:middle line:84%
from me is we talked at
the beginning of the show

00:53:49.100 --> 00:53:53.170 align:middle line:84%
about the ego, and the
ego being a behavior.

00:53:53.170 --> 00:53:56.590 align:middle line:84%
But it's not a tangible,
physical thing.

00:53:56.590 --> 00:54:03.590 align:middle line:84%
What is the difference between
the ego and love that is also

00:54:03.590 --> 00:54:07.120 align:middle line:90%
non-tangible, it is a behavior.

00:54:07.120 --> 00:54:08.444 align:middle line:90%
What's the difference?

00:54:08.444 --> 00:54:09.110 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: Right.

00:54:09.110 --> 00:54:09.990 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:54:09.990 --> 00:54:25.060 align:middle line:84%
So the difference has to do
with the source of the energy.

00:54:25.060 --> 00:54:28.630 align:middle line:84%
So what I'm going to say
now is incredibly black

00:54:28.630 --> 00:54:30.930 align:middle line:90%
and white and oversimplistic.

00:54:30.930 --> 00:54:36.760 align:middle line:84%
But one dimension of you
and me and everybody we know

00:54:36.760 --> 00:54:39.390 align:middle line:84%
is conditioning,
which is the way

00:54:39.390 --> 00:54:41.360 align:middle line:90%
that a computer is programmed.

00:54:41.360 --> 00:54:44.794 align:middle line:84%
If you program a computer in
a certain way, it stores code.

00:54:44.794 --> 00:54:46.210 align:middle line:84%
And then if you
click this button,

00:54:46.210 --> 00:54:49.050 align:middle line:84%
you can be absolutely sure
what the result will be.

00:54:49.050 --> 00:54:52.070 align:middle line:84%
If you click the button that
says Print, lo and behold,

00:54:52.070 --> 00:54:53.472 align:middle line:90%
the printer starts printing.

00:54:53.472 --> 00:54:55.180 align:middle line:84%
Now it's not that
sometimes you hit Print

00:54:55.180 --> 00:54:56.760 align:middle line:90%
and the shower comes on.

00:54:56.760 --> 00:54:59.420 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes you hit Print
and the sprinkler system

00:54:59.420 --> 00:55:00.390 align:middle line:90%
goes on in the garden.

00:55:00.390 --> 00:55:03.119 align:middle line:84%
You hit Print, every single
time you get the same result.

00:55:03.119 --> 00:55:03.910 align:middle line:90%
That's conditioned.

00:55:03.910 --> 00:55:05.610 align:middle line:90%
It's programmed, right.

00:55:05.610 --> 00:55:07.700 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's a lot of
things about human beings

00:55:07.700 --> 00:55:09.105 align:middle line:84%
that are conditioned,
and there's

00:55:09.105 --> 00:55:10.105 align:middle line:90%
nothing wrong with that.

00:55:10.105 --> 00:55:11.870 align:middle line:90%
It's perfectly good.

00:55:11.870 --> 00:55:14.040 align:middle line:84%
When I walk over to
the door, I don't

00:55:14.040 --> 00:55:16.052 align:middle line:84%
have to learn again how
to use a door handle.

00:55:16.052 --> 00:55:17.010 align:middle line:90%
It's conditioned in me.

00:55:17.010 --> 00:55:17.954 align:middle line:90%
I reach out.

00:55:17.954 --> 00:55:18.870 align:middle line:90%
I don't have to think.

00:55:18.870 --> 00:55:20.084 align:middle line:90%
Same thing with a car.

00:55:20.084 --> 00:55:21.500 align:middle line:84%
I don't have to
learn how to drive

00:55:21.500 --> 00:55:22.690 align:middle line:90%
the car every time I get in.

00:55:22.690 --> 00:55:26.360 align:middle line:84%
I know how to operate the
clutch and all that, right?

00:55:26.360 --> 00:55:28.936 align:middle line:84%
So that's one level of you
and me and everybody we know

00:55:28.936 --> 00:55:29.520 align:middle line:90%
is condition.

00:55:29.520 --> 00:55:30.614 align:middle line:90%
In that way we're robotic.

00:55:30.614 --> 00:55:32.030 align:middle line:84%
We're actually--
we're pretty much

00:55:32.030 --> 00:55:34.880 align:middle line:90%
like conditioned computers.

00:55:34.880 --> 00:55:37.460 align:middle line:84%
But there is another dimension
to you and me and everybody

00:55:37.460 --> 00:55:40.990 align:middle line:84%
we know which you
don't have to go

00:55:40.990 --> 00:55:43.310 align:middle line:84%
through a long journey
of completely getting

00:55:43.310 --> 00:55:45.400 align:middle line:84%
rid of the first one to
get to the second one.

00:55:45.400 --> 00:55:47.980 align:middle line:84%
It's there all the time,
which is spontaneous.

00:55:47.980 --> 00:55:52.390 align:middle line:90%


00:55:52.390 --> 00:55:53.584 align:middle line:90%
It's hard to find the words.

00:55:53.584 --> 00:55:55.750 align:middle line:84%
And it's good that it's
hard to find the right words

00:55:55.750 --> 00:55:58.880 align:middle line:84%
because we're talking
about a realm that is not

00:55:58.880 --> 00:56:01.912 align:middle line:84%
within the realm-- it's
not within the prison

00:56:01.912 --> 00:56:02.970 align:middle line:90%
of conditioned language.

00:56:02.970 --> 00:56:04.060 align:middle line:90%
It's free.

00:56:04.060 --> 00:56:06.230 align:middle line:84%
But-- so let's call it like
this, like an eruption,

00:56:06.230 --> 00:56:09.020 align:middle line:90%
like a spurting out of nothing.

00:56:09.020 --> 00:56:11.330 align:middle line:84%
It's like quantum physics,
you see, there's nothing.

00:56:11.330 --> 00:56:14.460 align:middle line:84%
And out of absolutely
nothing arises something.

00:56:14.460 --> 00:56:16.940 align:middle line:84%
This is the Heisenberg's
Uncertainty Principle,

00:56:16.940 --> 00:56:19.980 align:middle line:84%
there's a wave and then the
wave just becomes a particle

00:56:19.980 --> 00:56:23.400 align:middle line:84%
through observation that
was not there before.

00:56:23.400 --> 00:56:25.630 align:middle line:84%
So when you-- you've
got a beautiful husband

00:56:25.630 --> 00:56:26.986 align:middle line:90%
and a beautiful daughter.

00:56:26.986 --> 00:56:28.610 align:middle line:84%
When you're together
with your family--

00:56:28.610 --> 00:56:31.040 align:middle line:84%
and I've seen you with your
family-- you look at them

00:56:31.040 --> 00:56:32.651 align:middle line:84%
and then I'm sure
you've seen this.

00:56:32.651 --> 00:56:34.400 align:middle line:84%
And you might just
suddenly say something.

00:56:34.400 --> 00:56:36.970 align:middle line:84%
You might look at your
daughter and look at her

00:56:36.970 --> 00:56:38.780 align:middle line:84%
and then she'll speak
something, and you

00:56:38.780 --> 00:56:40.196 align:middle line:84%
don't know what
she's going to say

00:56:40.196 --> 00:56:42.240 align:middle line:90%
and it's completely spontaneous.

00:56:42.240 --> 00:56:44.370 align:middle line:84%
And that's actually
mostly what humor is.

00:56:44.370 --> 00:56:46.550 align:middle line:84%
You see, when we
enjoy humor together,

00:56:46.550 --> 00:56:49.754 align:middle line:84%
it's usually we laugh when
somebody says something

00:56:49.754 --> 00:56:51.170 align:middle line:84%
that was completely
unpredictable.

00:56:51.170 --> 00:56:52.970 align:middle line:84%
You could never have guessed
what they were going to say.

00:56:52.970 --> 00:56:55.250 align:middle line:84%
Unless it's like a
rehearsed joke or something.

00:56:55.250 --> 00:56:57.690 align:middle line:84%
But if we're just-- sorry,
didn't mean to interrupt you.

00:56:57.690 --> 00:56:59.440 align:middle line:84%
But if we're just
fooling around together,

00:56:59.440 --> 00:57:01.832 align:middle line:84%
that's why we laugh, because
somebody says something

00:57:01.832 --> 00:57:03.040 align:middle line:90%
you could not have predicted.

00:57:03.040 --> 00:57:06.834 align:middle line:84%
So all the time these two
dimensions are going on.

00:57:06.834 --> 00:57:08.500 align:middle line:84%
Well, actually there's
three dimensions.

00:57:08.500 --> 00:57:11.990 align:middle line:84%
There's also the physical body
that has its own conditioning.

00:57:11.990 --> 00:57:13.660 align:middle line:84%
But that's more
biological conditioning,

00:57:13.660 --> 00:57:15.540 align:middle line:90%
that's not social conditioning.

00:57:15.540 --> 00:57:17.561 align:middle line:84%
So you've got the
body that wants

00:57:17.561 --> 00:57:19.394 align:middle line:84%
to pee when it wants
to pee and wants to eat

00:57:19.394 --> 00:57:20.852 align:middle line:84%
and wants to sleep,
and then you've

00:57:20.852 --> 00:57:23.280 align:middle line:84%
got this conditioned
thoughts, and then

00:57:23.280 --> 00:57:28.240 align:middle line:84%
deeper than that there is the
eruption of pure spontaneity.

00:57:28.240 --> 00:57:30.220 align:middle line:90%
And all three co-exist, you see.

00:57:30.220 --> 00:57:34.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so it could erupt
as ego, it could erupt as love?

00:57:34.590 --> 00:57:36.480 align:middle line:90%
>>ARDAGH: No, no, no.

00:57:36.480 --> 00:57:39.267 align:middle line:84%
What you're calling ego
is a way of describing

00:57:39.267 --> 00:57:40.350 align:middle line:90%
this conditioned behavior.

00:57:40.350 --> 00:57:41.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, got it.

00:57:41.720 --> 00:57:44.290 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: Which is conditioned
towards being small, being

00:57:44.290 --> 00:57:44.910 align:middle line:90%
separate.

00:57:44.910 --> 00:57:46.840 align:middle line:84%
Because it feels
small and separate,

00:57:46.840 --> 00:57:49.140 align:middle line:84%
so it gets manipulative,
it gets competitive,

00:57:49.140 --> 00:57:50.330 align:middle line:90%
it's willing to tell lies.

00:57:50.330 --> 00:57:51.310 align:middle line:90%
It does all this stuff.

00:57:51.310 --> 00:57:55.450 align:middle line:84%
But it's understandable because
it has defined itself as me.

00:57:55.450 --> 00:57:55.950 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:57:55.950 --> 00:57:57.150 align:middle line:90%
It said, I'm a me.

00:57:57.150 --> 00:57:59.260 align:middle line:84%
It's all based on
the idea of me,

00:57:59.260 --> 00:58:01.400 align:middle line:90%
which you also can't find that.

00:58:01.400 --> 00:58:02.860 align:middle line:90%
You can't find the ego.

00:58:02.860 --> 00:58:05.380 align:middle line:90%
You can't find the I or the me.

00:58:05.380 --> 00:58:06.370 align:middle line:90%
You can talk about it.

00:58:06.370 --> 00:58:08.340 align:middle line:84%
You can't actually
directly experience it.

00:58:08.340 --> 00:58:09.160 align:middle line:90%
Nobody ever has.

00:58:09.160 --> 00:58:09.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:58:09.970 --> 00:58:12.286 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: So this idea
of me as separate,

00:58:12.286 --> 00:58:13.910 align:middle line:84%
as soon as you think
of yourself as me,

00:58:13.910 --> 00:58:17.120 align:middle line:84%
separate, now everybody
else is a threat.

00:58:17.120 --> 00:58:19.910 align:middle line:84%
So I've got to cheat a little
bit and lie a little bit,

00:58:19.910 --> 00:58:21.130 align:middle line:90%
manipulate a little bit.

00:58:21.130 --> 00:58:23.640 align:middle line:84%
All of that behavior--
it's not wrong--

00:58:23.640 --> 00:58:26.330 align:middle line:84%
it's completely the
inevitable byproduct

00:58:26.330 --> 00:58:28.790 align:middle line:84%
of thinking of yourself
as small and separate.

00:58:28.790 --> 00:58:30.520 align:middle line:84%
Then you have to
behave that way.

00:58:30.520 --> 00:58:31.300 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:58:31.300 --> 00:58:34.030 align:middle line:84%
But the other dimension of
you, which is always here,

00:58:34.030 --> 00:58:36.230 align:middle line:84%
which is infinite,
which is spacious,

00:58:36.230 --> 00:58:38.250 align:middle line:84%
which needs nothing
from everybody,

00:58:38.250 --> 00:58:40.940 align:middle line:84%
which has everything
to give to everybody,

00:58:40.940 --> 00:58:43.000 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't need to
manipulate or lie at all.

00:58:43.000 --> 00:58:44.120 align:middle line:90%
It's free.

00:58:44.120 --> 00:58:47.100 align:middle line:84%
And we don't-- this
is the big catch,

00:58:47.100 --> 00:58:50.770 align:middle line:84%
you don't have to get rid of one
in order to access the other.

00:58:50.770 --> 00:58:53.190 align:middle line:84%
You can accept that
they all coexist.

00:58:53.190 --> 00:58:55.640 align:middle line:84%
And the more you
relax, actually,

00:58:55.640 --> 00:58:57.780 align:middle line:84%
into recognizing
the spaciousness,

00:58:57.780 --> 00:59:00.020 align:middle line:84%
the more you can be
humorous about little quirks

00:59:00.020 --> 00:59:02.920 align:middle line:84%
of the conditioning
and laugh about it.

00:59:02.920 --> 00:59:06.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I'm nearly 60 and,
you know, I'm British.

00:59:06.770 --> 00:59:07.970 align:middle line:90%
And I do British things.

00:59:07.970 --> 00:59:10.200 align:middle line:90%
I say things in a British way.

00:59:10.200 --> 00:59:12.640 align:middle line:84%
If somebody bangs
into me, I say, sorry.

00:59:12.640 --> 00:59:13.520 align:middle line:90%
Oh, sorry.

00:59:13.520 --> 00:59:15.700 align:middle line:84%
It's just British
conditioning, you see?

00:59:15.700 --> 00:59:18.490 align:middle line:90%
Well, you can laugh about that.

00:59:18.490 --> 00:59:21.410 align:middle line:84%
My kids, you know,
they-- we were in-- we

00:59:21.410 --> 00:59:24.640 align:middle line:84%
were together in
TLC this summer.

00:59:24.640 --> 00:59:29.230 align:middle line:84%
And our mutual friend, Chris
Atwood, he asked my son,

00:59:29.230 --> 00:59:31.960 align:middle line:84%
Abby, he said, well, so how
was it being raised by Arjuna?

00:59:31.960 --> 00:59:33.086 align:middle line:90%
I guess they were curious.

00:59:33.086 --> 00:59:34.460 align:middle line:84%
What kind of dad
would Arjuna be?

00:59:34.460 --> 00:59:35.876 align:middle line:84%
How was it being
raised by Arjuna?

00:59:35.876 --> 00:59:38.040 align:middle line:84%
My son looked up for a
minute and he said, well,

00:59:38.040 --> 00:59:41.302 align:middle line:84%
it was basically a series
of awkward moments.

00:59:41.302 --> 00:59:45.329 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a great answer.

00:59:45.329 --> 00:59:47.370 align:middle line:84%
>>ARDAGH: So, you see, we
have our personalities,

00:59:47.370 --> 00:59:51.610 align:middle line:84%
but the more you can rest in
this undefined spaciousness,

00:59:51.610 --> 00:59:54.090 align:middle line:84%
the more you just laugh
about the idiosyncrasies

00:59:54.090 --> 00:59:56.670 align:middle line:84%
of the conditioning, you
don't have to make it go away.

00:59:56.670 --> 00:59:58.560 align:middle line:84%
It's all just
happily coexisting.

